job. When a new note is created the system will time and date stamp the note. notes can also be emailed directly out of the Crashzone system. The information only appears on the details page and does not show on the quote. Notes is a useful tool to track important information.\r\n<em>* To activate Notes go to the settings page ( for existing customers )\r\n* Click on the Show note Tick box\r\n* Scroll down to the bottom of the settings page and click submit</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/cz-notes.JPG\" alt=\"Crashzone Activate Notes\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/09/02/crashzone-new-feature-note/','2008-09-02 05:15:26','2008-09-02 05:15:26',NULL),(554,'Crashzone new feature - AutoComplete','crashzone-new-feature-autocomplete','Crashzone new feature - AutoComplete','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/cz-autocomplete.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone AutoComplete\" /> \r\n\r\n<strong>AutoComplete</strong> is a useful tool which remembers previously entered information in the details page. Using Autocomplete will help speed up your quotation time and reduce the amount of typing required. Type the first letters and choose the owner from the autocomplete list, which will then complete all fields. AutoComplete is activated from the settings page for existing customers. For reference go to the Crashzone help page and view \"<em>How do i start a new quote</em>\"',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/08/25/crashzone-new-feature-autocomplete/','2008-08-25 10:39:23','2008-08-25 10:40:37',NULL),(564,'How to activate AutoComplete','how-to-activate-autocomplete','How to activate AutoComplete','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/cz-settings-page.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone settings page AutoComplete\" />\r\nTo Activate the <strong>AutoComplete</strong> feature click on the <em>settings</em> link located at the top right of the page in Crashzone. Once in the settings page Click on the <em>AutoText</em> tick box and then scroll down and click submit. The AutoComplete feature is now active and ready to use on your next quote.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/08/26/how-to-activate-autocomplete/','2008-08-26 08:00:15','2008-08-26 08:00:15',NULL),(565,'Crashzone at Campbelltown TAFE','crashzone-at-campbeltown-tafe','Crashzone at Campbelltown TAFE','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/campbeltown-tafe.jpg\" alt=\"Campbeltown TAFE\" />\r\n\r\nCrashzone at Campbelltown TAFE doing a demonstration for the panel beating and spray painting students. With Crashzone each student can have their own system that they can use in the class room and at home. Pictured above Winston Okeefe and Head teacher Tom Vukelic.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/08/29/crashzone-at-campbeltown-tafe/','2008-08-29 05:14:24','2008-08-29 05:20:05',NULL),(567,'Crashzone update 31/08/2008','crashzone-update-31082008','Crashzone update 31/08/2008','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/04/sm.jpg\" alt=\"sm.jpg\" />\r\n\r\nSome customer have reported that information is being dropped from their quotations after they have been completed. The problem has now been identified and will be rectified ASAP. Anyone experiencing problems please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\">support@crashzone.com.au</a> or phone 1300 721 090',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/08/30/crashzone-update-31082008/','2008-08-30 02:35:10','2008-08-30 02:35:10',NULL),(568,'Crashzone system updated - 31/08/2008','crashzone-system-updated-31082008','Crashzone system updated - 31/08/2008','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/04/sm.jpg\" alt=\"sm.jpg\" />\r\n\r\nAn update has been made to Crashzone to rectify a problem with information being lost of quotes. The update was uploaded on the 31/08/2008 and the system is operating as normal. If any customer experiences problems with the Crashzone system please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\">support@crashzone.com.au</a> or phone 1300 721 090',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/08/31/crashzone-system-updated-31082008/','2008-08-31 14:06:26','2008-08-31 14:06:26',NULL),(569,'Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies','Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','To help with the update of the Crashzone system please delete your temporary files and cookies. This helps refresh the system and allows the update to work correctly.\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/delete-temp-files.JPG\" alt=\"Delete temp files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/firefox.JPG\" alt=\"Delete temp files and cookies firefox\" />\r\n\r\nPlease note if it has been awhile since the files have been deleted it may take your computer a few minutes to complete the task. Please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090 if you are experiencing any problems or need further help.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/08/31/web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies/','2008-08-31 14:06:58','2008-08-31 14:06:58',NULL),(574,'The National Collision Repairer Magazine - at John Hunter Car Repairs','the-national-collision-repairer-magazine-at-johh-hunter-car-repairs','The National Collision Repairer Magazine - at John Hunter Car Repairs',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/david-newton-ross-1a.jpg\" alt=\"David Newton Ross at John Hunter Car Repairs\" />\r\nFrom the left: John Hunter, Winston Okeefe &amp; David Newton Ross\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/david-newton-ross-4.jpg\" alt=\"David Newton Ross at John Hunter Car repairs\" />\r\nDavid Newton Ross from The National Collision Repairer magazine Catching up with John Hunter Car Repairs. John Hunter Car Repairs will appear in an upcoming issue of The National Collision Repairer. A big thank you to David for dropping in to see us.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/09/03/the-national-collision-repairer-magazine-at-johh-hunter-car-repairs/','2008-09-03 10:34:47','2008-09-03 11:16:12',NULL),(582,'Titan Air Jack - blows itself up ','titan-air-jack-blows-itself-up','Titan Air Jack - blows itself up ','Self lifting air jack powered by your own exhaust. An easy way to lift your car, 4wd or truck with up to 30 inches of lift. Place the deflated bag under the vehicle, connect the jack to your exhaust and start the engine. The bag inflates and lifts the car allowing you to easily change a tyre, it can even be used on soft surfaces such as sand. Check out the video of the jack in use.\r\n\r\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/OsnwVCOiIp4&hl=en&fs=1\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/OsnwVCOiIp4&hl=en&fs=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\"></embed></object>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/09/04/titan-air-jack-blows-itself-up/','2008-09-04 14:17:40','2008-09-04 14:17:40',NULL),(585,'Crashzone Thank you ','crashzone-thank-you','Crashzone Thank you ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/smiley2.jpg\" alt=\"Smiley Face\" />\r\n\r\nA big thank you to Vicky at Marinos Supreme Panel beaters for helping Crashzone fix the recent bug found in the system.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/09/05/crashzone-thank-you/','2008-09-05 10:32:32','2008-09-05 10:32:32',NULL),(592,'Crashzone new feature - Quote date','crashzone-new-feature-quote-date','Crashzone new feature - Quote date','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/cz-quote-date.JPG\" alt=\"Crashzone quote date on printed quote\" />\r\nFrom the feedback that we have received from our customers the quote date has now been added to the viewed quote. Quote date is based on the day that the quote was written or modified.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/09/09/crashzone-new-feature-quote-date/','2008-09-09 10:01:21','2008-09-09 10:01:21',NULL),(593,'Crashzone - iRoad on iPhone ','crashzone-iroad-on-iphone','Crashzone - iRoad on iPhone ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/iphone1.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone iRoad running on a iPhone\" />\r\n\r\nThe latest on offer from Crashzone \"iR<em>oad 1</em><em>.0\"</em>  for the Apple iPhone. You can now use your iPhone to look up quotes on Crashzone. A fast and convenient way to keep track of your quotes. For more information please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\">support@crashzone.com.au</a> or phone 1300 721 090\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/iroad-2.JPG\" alt=\"Crashzone iRoad on iPhone\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2008/09/10/crashzone-iroad-on-iphone/','2008-09-10 11:55:11','2008-09-12 05:53:05',NULL),(597,'Insurance labour rates - National list ','insurance-labour-rates-national-list','Insurance labour rates - National list ','Crashzone is attempting to put together a national list of insurance rates set by the various insurance companies. To make this possible we would like to in list the help of our customers to acquire the correct rates. Click on