-bodyshop-news-december-2008/','2009-01-13 03:36:22','2009-01-13 03:36:22',NULL),(1241,'Crashzone ORM - coming soon ','crashzone-orm-coming-soon','Crashzone ORM - coming soon ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/crashzone-orm-2.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone ORM coming soon\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Crashzone ORM module is currently going through the certification process with ORM and will be customer ready soon. Crashzone will update customers as soon as the ORM module is ready to use. Please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\">support@crashzone.com.au</a> or phone 1300 721 090  if you have any questions or concerns. For more information about ORM please visit  <a href=\"http://www.repairnetwork.com.au/index.html\">http://www.repairnetwork.com.au/index.html</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/01/15/crashzone-orm-coming-soon/','2009-01-15 03:18:46','2009-01-15 03:18:46',NULL),(1246,'Crashzone login - remember me ','crashzone-login-remember-me','Crashzone login - remember me ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/crashzone-login-1.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone login - remember me\" />\r\n\r\nUse the \"remember me\" function on the front page of Crashzone to speed up the login process. When remember me is ticked you will not need to type in your email address and password each time you go into Crashzone.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/01/16/crashzone-login-remember-me/','2009-01-16 04:02:41','2009-01-16 04:02:41',NULL),(1249,'GM cancelled Cadillac for Australia','gm-cancelled-cadillac-for-australia','GM cancelled Cadillac for Australia','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/cadillac-australia.jpg\" alt=\"Cadillac Australia\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">GM Holden announced that the premium brand Cadillac will not be coming to Australia. GM Holden managing director, Mark Reuss   quoted \"given the economic climate in Australia and worldwide it was not the right time to be launching a luxury niche brand here\". For more information visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/\">http://www.caradvice.com.au/</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/01/22/gm-cancelled-cadillac-for-australia/','2009-01-22 07:05:47','2009-01-22 07:05:47',NULL),(1252,'2009 Collision Repair Expo','2009-collision-repair-expo','2009 Collision Repair Expo','\r\n<p align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial\" lang=\"EN-AU\"><font class=\"tx_content_head_orange\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/2009-collision-repair-expo.jpg\" alt=\"2009 Collision Repair Expo\" /></font></span></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial\" lang=\"EN-AU\"><font class=\"tx_content\">Visit the 2009 Collision Repair Exo to see the industry leaders showcasing 100s of new products and solutions. </font></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial\" lang=\"EN-AU\"><font class=\"tx_content\">The 2009 trade shows being hosted by the Australian Automotive Aftermarket Association (AAAA) from 2 to 4 April at the Sydney Exhibition Centre will be the largest and most comprehensive automotive trade event ever held in <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Australia</st1:place></st1:country-region>. Come along and see Crashzone at stand E25 </font></span></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial\" lang=\"EN-AU\"> <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/tradeshow-group-photo.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone Tradeshow Group Photo\" /></span></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/01/23/2009-collision-repair-expo/','2009-01-23 08:08:05','2009-01-23 08:08:05',NULL),(1255,'Happy Australia day 2009','happy-australia-day-2009','Happy Australia day 2009','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/cz-australia-day.jpg\" alt=