 Computing all Crashzone customers can type in the coupon code ‘crashzone’ to receive $100.00 ex.GST/$110 inc.GST off the advertised price for a new Motion Computing Tablet PC! Motion Computing Tablet PC’s increase the productivity of workflow for Smash Repairers by reducing the need for double keying of data and enabling them to work from anywhere. This coupon only applies to the new Motion Computing J3400 and Motion Computing F5 Tablet PC models purchased from <a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/\">www.workflowcomputing.com.au</a> until July 31st, 2009.  (These Motion Computing Tablet PC models are currently used by QBE, Allianz and Suncorp motor vehicle assessors).\r\nMotion Computing Tablet PC’s are fully compatible with Crashzone, and Workflow Computing would be happy to arrange a product demonstration for you. For more information please visit <a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/\">www.workflowcomputing.com.au</a> or phone 02 9029 8056\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-motion-j3400.jpg\" alt=\"Motion J3400 in action\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/07/03/workflow-computing-motion-tablet-pc/','2009-07-03 05:45:12','2009-07-03 05:49:08',NULL),(1579,'New Times And Rates ( NTAR ) update ','new-times-and-rates-ntar-update','New Times And Rates ( NTAR ) update ',' <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/smashed-vp-commodore.jpg\" title=\"Smashed Vp Commodore\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/smashed-vp-commodore.jpg\" alt=\"Smashed Vp Commodore\" /></a>\r\n\r\nNTAR has released a major update ( 02.07.2009 ) to adjust the new times and rates based on the past 6 months of review. Some times have gone up and some times are down. The latest NTAR times have been integrated into the Crashzone system now. For more information or help with quoting new times and rates please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/07/09/new-times-and-rates-ntar-update/','2009-07-09 05:04:34','2009-07-09 05:04:34',NULL),(1583,'Tax break boosts new car sales','tax-break-boosts-new-car-sales','Tax break boosts new car sales',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/new-vehicles.jpg\" alt=\"New vehicles sales\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">New car sales rebounded strongly in June, driven by the Federal Government’s tax breaks for business vehicle purchases. Business sales were up 12 per cent over last June, pushing the overall market to 102,847 sales. To read the full article please visit <a href=\"http://www.drive.com.au/Editorial/ArticleDetail.aspx?ArticleID=64111&amp;vf=2\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/07/07/tax-break-boosts-new-car-sales/','2009-07-07 06:08:54','2009-07-07 06:08:54',NULL),(1587,'Crashzone how to create a supplement quote ','crashzone-how-to-do-a-supplement-quote','Crashzone how to create a supplement quote ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-create-new-supplement-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement quote\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-new-supplement-button.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement button\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"> To create a new supplement click on the drop down box in the quote page and select new. This will generate a blank supplement, in this example quote 2.1</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-items.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement items\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Write the supplement quote and from the view page you can view the supplement quote and the original quote. When invoicing any supplements will be added to the original quote to give a grand total.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplemen