greater than a regular seatbelt. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/45670/ford-unveils-seatbelt-airbags-due-in-new-models-from-late-2010/#title\">www.themotorreport.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/09/seatbelt-airbags/','2009-11-09 05:11:24','2009-11-09 05:11:24',NULL),(1746,'How to print a quote in dollars $','how-to-print-a-quote-in-dollars','How to print a quote in dollars $',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/cz-print-in.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone printing quote in dollars $\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>Q</strong>: I have written my quote in hours can I print or email the quote in dollars ?</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>A:</strong> Crashzone makes it easy to convert the quote from hours to dollars, from the view page click on the <strong>dollar tick box</strong>. The estimate will change from hours to dollar format and is now ready to be printed or emailed.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/10/how-to-print-a-quote-in-dollars/','2009-11-10 07:30:56','2009-11-10 07:30:56',NULL),(1748,'Lexus LFA','lexus-lfa','Lexus LFA',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/lexus-lfa.jpg\" alt=\"Lexus LFA supercar\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Lexus LFA produces 412kW at 8,700rpm and 480Nm of torque at 6,800rpm Redlining at 9000rpm. The LFA is capable of going 0-100km/h in 3.7 seconds and before hitting a top speed of 325km/h. Lexus\'s new supercar weighs in at 1480kg. This is achieved by using carbon fibre reinforced plastic (CFRP) for 65 percent of its body. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.webwombat.com.au/motoring/news_reports/lexus-lfa.htm\">www.webwombat.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/11/lexus-lfa/','2009-11-11 06:33:24','2009-11-11 06:33:24',NULL),(1750,'Volkswagen - worlds largest vehicle producer','volkswagen-worlds-largest-vehicle-producer','Volkswagen - worlds largest vehicle producer',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/vollkswagen.jpg\" alt=\"Volkswagen - worlds largest vehicle producer\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Volkswagen has overtaken Toyota as the world’s largest vehicle producer for the first three-quarters of 2009. VW made 4.4 million vehicles from January to September compared to Toyota\'s 4.2 million cars. For the full story visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/47598/volkswagen-tops-toyota-as-worlds-largest-vehicle-producer/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/16/volkswagen-worlds-largest-vehicle-producer/','2009-11-16 02:00:13','2009-11-16 02:00:13',NULL),(1752,'Crashzone - Parts prices ','crashzone-parts-prices','Crashzone - Parts prices ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/crashzone-parts-prices.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone parts prices\" />\r\n\r\nCrashzone now has FREE part numbers and prices.\r\n\r\nCrashzone is working hard to setup all of our users to have access to this new module and we have been emailing customers once the module has been switched on. If you have not received an email and user manual yet, and would like access to parts numbers and prices please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/12/crashzone-parts-prices/','2009-11-12 06:52:21','2009-11-12 06:52:21',NULL),(1754,'Rally car crashes','rally-car-crashes','Rally car crashes','<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/R5NEnwp13g4&color1=0xb1b1b1&color2=0xcfcfcf&hl=en&feature=player_embedded&fs=1\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/R5NEnwp13g4&color1=0xb1b1b1&color2=0xcfcfcf&hl=en&feature=player_embedded&fs=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowScriptAccess=\"always\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\"></embed></object>\r\n\r\nLots of rally cars crashing at high speed.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/17/rally-car-crashes/','2009-11-17 06:15:46','2009-11-17 06:15:46',NULL),(1755,'Crashzone how to add images to the quote','crashzone-how-to-add-images-to-the-quote-2','Crashzone how to add images to the quote','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-adding-images-3.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - adding images to the quote\" />\r\n\r\nAdding images to your quote is done by email\r\n\r\n* Open a new email\r\n* Type in you Crashzone email address\r\n* Type the Crashzone quote number into the subject i.e ( 5013 )\r\n* Attach images to the email\r\n* Send email\r\n* Images will now attach to the quote  ( the process takes approx 1 minute )\r\n* Click on the details tab to refresh the system and load the new images\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-images-on-details-page.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - images on details page\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/19/crashzone-how-to-add-images-to-the-quote-2/','2009-11-19 06:56:04','2009-11-19 06:56:04',NULL),(1757,'Ford FPV F6  ','ford-fpv-f6','Ford FPV F6  ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/ford-f6.jpg\" alt=\"Ford FPV F6\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">With 310kW of power and 565Nm of torque available from just 1950rpm, the all-new F6 delivers in-gear acceleration that has to be experienced to be believed. for the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/48162/fpv-f6-310-review-road-test/\">caradvice.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/22/ford-fpv-f6/','2009-11-22 06:16:34','2009-11-23 05:15:42',NULL),(1758,'Crashzone - bigpond users','crashzone-bigpond-users','Crashzone - bigpond users',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/04/sm.jpg\" alt=\"sm.jpg\" />\r\n\r\nTelstra Bigpond user in WA have reported that they are having trouble to login into Crashzone this afternoon 20/11/2009. This appears to be a fault with Telstra and we suggest any customers experiencing problems to contact Telstra and report the fault. For more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/20/crashzone-bigpond-users/','2009-11-20 08:36:29','2009-11-20 08:36:29',NULL),(1760,'HID headlights','hid-headlights','HID headlights','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/hid.jpg\" alt=\"HID headlamps\" />\r\n\r\nHID headlights use a high-voltage electrical arc that vaporises metallic salts to produce a much brighter light. They also contain xenon gas, which is used to quickly bring the process up to operating temperature. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.drive.com.au/Editorial/ArticleDetail.aspx?ArticleID=67243&amp;vf=3\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/07/hid-headlights/','2009-12-07 00:22:40','2009-12-07 00:22:40',NULL),(1761,'Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-6','Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','\r\n<p align=\"left\">Maintenance of your web browser may be required on occasion. By deleting temporary files and cookies it allows Crashzone to do a fresh reload next time you re start the system. Below is a quick guide on how to preform the maintenance on Internet Explorer and Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or further help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a> or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/10/web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-6/','2009-12-10 07:59:46','2009-12-10 07:59:46',NULL),(1762,'Faster internet','faster-internet','Faster internet','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/slow-internet.jpg\" alt=\"Slow internet\" />\r\nAre you paying top dollar for old technology Internet ?\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\">Many Australian businesses use Telstra bigpond as their Internet provider. In the past there was not a lot of choices and Telstra was the main player when it came to your Internet connection.  The problem is that the nature of the Internet has changed and your average business requires faster Internet and larger download limits than before. Many customers are still stuck with ADSL1 connections that are many times slower than your basic ADSL2 connection.  Telstra do offer the newer and faster ADSL2 connections but usually the price is no where as competitive as the other major providers. Two ISP that offer ADSL2 and provide fast and reliable Internet are iinet and TPG.\r\nTo test your Internet speed visit <a href=\"http://www.zdnet.com.au/broadband/speedtest.htm\">http://www.zdnet.com.au/broadband/speedtest.htm</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.iinet.net.au/customers/\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/iinet2.jpg\" alt=\"iinet\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.tpg.com.au/\" title=\"TPG\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/tpg4.jpg\" alt=\"TPG\" style=\"width: 108px; height: 58px\" height=\"59\" width=\"112\" /></a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/26/faster-internet/','2009-11-26 12:13:30','2009-11-26 12:13:30',NULL),(1763,'Go mobile with Crashzone','go-mobile-with-crashzone-2','Go mobile with Crashzone','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/crashzone-mobile.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone Mobile with Motion Tablet J3400\" />\r\n\r\nUsing Crashzone with a tablet PC or laptop allow you to quote anywhere anytime. Write quotes while in front of the car all in real time. No setup or software required just go to www.crashzone.com.au and login to your account and your mobile. For more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/30/go-mobile-with-crashzone-2/','2009-11-30 05:33:09','2009-11-30 05:33:09',NULL),(1764,'Workflow Computing - Motion tablet PC','workflow-computing-motion-tablet-pc-3','Workflow Computing - Motion tablet PC','<a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/workflow-computing.jpg\" alt=\"Workflow Computing\" /></a>\r\nThe Motion Computing product range provides compelling advantages over conventional computing products, including key features such as:\r\n- Guaranteed Outdoor Screen View ability,\r\n- Rugged enough to withstand rain, dust, and being dropped,\r\n- Fastest Mobile Broadband connectivity available in Australia.\r\n\r\nIf you haven’t used a Motion Computing Tablet PC before we can arrange loan units for evaluation purposes, if required. Call Workflow Computing to arrange a product demonstration today on (02) 9029-8056 <a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/\">workflowcomputing.com.au</a>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/rohan-from-workflow-computing.jpg\" alt=\"Rohan from Workflow Computing\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/03/workflow-computing-motion-tablet-pc-3/','2009-12-03 01:16:15','2009-12-03 01:16:15',NULL),(1765,'Crashzone notice - phone support','crashzone-notice-phone-support','Crashzone notice - phone support','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/04/sm.jpg\" alt=\"sm.jpg\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Notice to customers:</strong>\r\n<p align=\"left\"> Crashzone phone support will be limited from Wednesday the 25th of November to Monday 30th of November due to phone reception while travelling interstate. Where possible please email support@crashzone.com.au and our support team will help solve any issues or enquires.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/24/crashzone-notice-phone-support/','2009-11-24 08:15:15','2009-11-26 15:49:20',NULL),(1767,'Crashzone system','crashzone-system-3','Crashzone system','Crashzone system updated\r\n\r\n<strong>Crashzone Support</strong>',0,0,3,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/11/26/crashzone-system-3/','2009-11-26 02:54:50','2009-11-30 05:32:13',NULL),(1768,'Crashzone - EstImage coming soon','crashzone-estimage-coming-soon','Crashzone - EstImage coming soon',' <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/monaro-side-impact.jpg\" title=\"Holden Monaro side impact\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/monaro-side-impact.jpg\" alt=\"Holden Monaro side impact\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Crashzone now has approval from Stelvio to do EstImage integration. This means our programmers are now going full speed to get Crashzone customer ready for EstImage work. We would like to thank all of our customers that have supported Crashzone and stuck with us, even with insurance companies pressuring you to change. Crashzone will keep you updated on the integration progress. For more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/08/crashzone-estimage-coming-soon/','2009-12-08 07:12:43','2009-12-08 07:12:43',NULL),(1771,'BMW X6 M','bmw-x6-m','BMW X6 M','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/bmw-x6-m.jpg\" alt=\"BMW X6 M\" />\r\n\r\nThe BMW X6 M comes with a twin-turbocharged 4.4 litre petrol V8 which develops 408kW and 680Nm of torque, the latter of which is available from between 1500 and 5650 rpm. Performance is suitably brisk: the 0-100km/h sprint can be done away with in just 4.7 seconds. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/47305/2010-bmw-x6-m-launches-in-australia/#title\">themotorreport.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/11/bmw-x6-m/','2009-12-11 07:31:39','2009-12-11 07:31:39',NULL),(1773,'Google Chrome not compatible with Crashzone','google-chrome-not-compatible-with-crashzone','Google Chrome not compatible with Crashzone',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/system-update.jpg\" alt=\"Customer Notice:\" />\r\n\r\nGoogle Chrome web browser is not compatible with Crashzone. Crashzone recommends using either Mozilla Firefox or Internet Explorer to run Crashzone. If you are using Google Chrome and don\'t know how to swap back to Internet Explorer please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/google-chrome.jpg\" alt=\"Google Chrome\" />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/personal.html\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Mozilla Firefox\" /></a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/14/google-chrome-not-compatible-with-crashzone/','2009-12-14 02:52:27','2009-12-14 02:52:27',NULL),(1775,'Ford Explorer - crusie control ','ford-explorer-crusie-control','Ford Explorer - crusie control ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/ford-explorer.jpg\" alt=\"Ford Explorer\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">A terrified 22-year-old driver thought he was going to die when a jammed cruise control trapped him in his four-wheel drive for half an hour as it raced along the Eastern Freeway. The Ford Explorer’s cruise control got stuck at 100 kph. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.smh.com.au/national/cruise-control-terror-for-freeway-driver-20091215-ktxn.html?autostart=1\">smh.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/16/ford-explorer-crusie-control/','2009-12-16 02:06:32','2009-12-24 02:05:54',NULL),(1777,'Crashzone - Christmas closure notice','crashzone-christmas-closure-notice','Crashzone - Christmas closure notice',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2007/12/crashzone-christmas.JPG\" alt=\"Merry Christmas\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Dates for Christmas Closure: From Wednesday the 23rd of December 2009 to Monday the 4th of January 2010</strong>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Crashzone system will work as normal during this period and support will be available by emailing support@crashzone.com.au. I would like to take this opportunity to wish you a Happy Christmas and a Prosperous New Year on behalf of all the team at Crashzone. If you have any inquires please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/21/crashzone-christmas-closure-notice/','2009-12-21 00:26:00','2009-12-21 00:27:06',NULL),(1778,'Lexus active pedestrian detection system ','lexus-active-pedestrian-detection-system','Lexus active pedestrian detection system ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/lexus-ls460.jpg\" alt=\"Lexus LS460\" />\r\nIf the system detects no reaction from the driver, the APDS can initiate braking as the vehicle nears the object, as well as decreasing the steering ratio to increase the intensity and quickness of the steering response. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/47479/lexus-considering-active-pedestrian-detection-system-for-australia/#title\">themotorreport.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/17/lexus-active-pedestrian-detection-system/','2009-12-17 04:05:41','2009-12-17 04:05:41',NULL),(1780,'Aston Martin Cygnet','aston-martin-cygnet','Aston Martin Cygnet',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/aston-martin-cygnet.jpg\" alt=\"Aston Martin Cygnet\" />\r\n\r\nBased on the Toyota iQ city car, Aston Martin has revealed the production ready Aston Martin Cygnet. Featuring a higher grade of luxury and specification than any car in its class has seen before. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/47626/aston-martin-cygnet-revealed-in-production-form/#title\">themotorreport.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/06/aston-martin-cygnet/','2010-01-06 05:37:55','2010-01-06 05:37:55',NULL),(1783,'Mini Beachcomber','mini-beachcomber','Mini Beachcomber',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/mini-beachcomber.jpg\" alt=\"Mini Beachcomber\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Memories of the  door-less Mini Moke will be revived at January’s Detroit motor show with this  radical Mini concept. The Beachcomber uses all-wheel-drive and the tough off-road look is aided by an elevated ride height and 17-inch wheels wrapped in chunky off-road rubber and housed in bulky wheel-arches. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/doorless-mini-resurrects-the-moke-20091216-kvi0.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/24/mini-beachcomber/','2009-12-24 02:06:23','2009-12-24 02:06:23',NULL),(1784,'Crashzone - system maintenance','crashzone-system-maintenance','Crashzone - system maintenance','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2007/12/crashzone-christmas.JPG\" alt=\"Merry Christmas\" /> <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/system-update.jpg\" alt=\"routine system maintance\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Crashzone website will be temporarily down between Friday 25th of December 2009 to Monday the 28th of December 2009. The down time is necessary to preform scheduled maintenance and upgrades to the Crashzone system. During this time Crashzone maybe inaccessible. we apologise for any inconvenience and appreciate your understanding. If you have any questions in relation to this notice please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/25/crashzone-system-maintenance/','2009-12-25 02:29:33','2009-12-28 04:37:05',NULL),(1785,'Happy New Year 2010','happy-new-year-2010','Happy New Year 2010','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/crashzone_happy-new-year.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone happy new year\" />\r\n\r\nFrom everyone at Crashzone we wish you a happy and safe New Year and look forward to seeing you again in 2010.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2009/12/31/happy-new-year-2010/','2009-12-31 06:16:04','2009-12-31 06:16:04',NULL),(1786,'Crashzone - EstImage coming soon','crashzone-estimage-coming-soon-2','Crashzone - EstImage coming soon',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/car-on-autorobot.jpg\" alt=\"Car on AutoRobot\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Crashzone is currently doing certification testing for EstImage. As soon as the integration has approval by EstImage we will be setting up customers to go live.  Crashzone will keep customers updated on the progress. If you have any questions please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/04/crashzone-estimage-coming-soon-2/','2010-01-04 03:33:35','2010-01-04 03:33:35',NULL),(1789,'Fenix Automotive’s supercar','fenix-automotive%e2%80%99s-supercar','Fenix Automotive’s supercar','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/fenix.jpg\" alt=\"Fenix Automotive\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Fenix Automotive’s new supercar. With a target kerb weight of 1200kgs, Fenix estimates that the LS9-engined car should accelerate from 0-160km/h in under seven seconds on its way to a top speed of around 322km/h. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/52329/new-fenix-supercar-teaser-pics-released/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/07/fenix-automotive%e2%80%99s-supercar/','2010-01-07 07:47:01','2010-01-07 07:47:01',NULL),(1790,'Anti hoon law impound Lamborghini','anti-hoon-law-impound-lamborghini','Anti hoon law impound Lamborghini',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/lamborghini1.jpg\" alt=\"Yellow Lamborghini\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Patrick Nugawela, a GP in Perth\'s northern suburbs, had his $200,000 Lamborghini impounded after his mechanic was caught driving it at speeds up to 160km/h in a 90km/h. Under Western Australia\'s anti-hoon laws, police can impound any car exceeding the speed limit by more than 60km/h, even if it is not the property of the driver. For the full story please visit  <a href=\"http://smh.drive.com.au/motor-news/hoon-laws-put-lamborghinis-owner-on-the-highway-to-hell-20100108-lygm.html\">drive.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/11/anti-hoon-law-impound-lamborghini/','2010-01-11 01:20:30','2010-01-11 01:20:30',NULL),(1794,'Fake Police combat NSW speeding','fake-police-combat-nsw-speeding','Fake Police combat NSW speeding','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nsw-police-car.jpg\" alt=\"NSW Police Car\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Five decommissioned highway patrol cars have been used by New South Wales police to try to encourage good driving behaviour. A police spokeswoman said members of the Southern Region Highway Patrol thought “instead of keeping them in a car park before they get sold we’ll put them on the side of the road [so they can] act as a deterrent”. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/52844/decommissioned-cars-fake-police-combat-nsw-speeding/\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/12/fake-police-combat-nsw-speeding/','2010-01-12 03:39:59','2010-01-12 03:39:59',NULL),(1795,'Digital camera image size','digital-camera-image-size-3','Digital camera image size','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-image-size.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone image size setting on digital camera\" />\r\n\r\nWith most digital point-and-shoot cameras, you can actually choose a lower resolution than the camera’s advertised maximum, which is where it’s set when you take it out of the box. You do this by entering the shooting menu and selecting the “Image Size” or “Resolution” option. When you do that, you’ll see a series of number pairs such as these:\r\n\r\n* 3648 x 2736 or 10 megapixel ( 1.1 MB to 2.2 MB approx)\r\n* 3264 x 2448 or 8 megapixel ( 970 KB to 1.9 MB approx )\r\n* 2048 x 1536  or 3.1 megapixel ( 500 KB to 1 MB approx )\r\n* 1600 x 1200 or 1.9 megapixel ( 250 KB to 700KB approx )\r\n* 1280 x 960 or 1.2 megapixel ( 240 KB to 490 KB approx )\r\n* 1024 x 768 or 0.8 megapixel ( 170 KB to 350 KB approx )\r\n<strong>* 640 x 480 or VGA ( 75 KB to 150 KB approx )   - ORM, PNET, ARNIE setting\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nSetting a lower resolution level creates a smaller-sized picture file. When you adjust the resolution downward, you’ll see the little number on the viewing screen and/or LCD panel that tells you how many more pictures you can fit on the card go up and up. Set 640 x 480, and you’ll be able to fit hundreds if not thousands of pictures on a decent-sized memory card.\r\n\r\nWhen emailing images a lower/lowest setting on your camera is always best this will allow you send  images quickly and make it easier for your customer to download and store the images you send to them.\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with setting up your camera please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/13/digital-camera-image-size-3/','2010-01-13 08:10:53','2010-01-13 08:10:53',NULL),(1796,'NSW state wide 90km/h speed limit ','nsw-state-wide-90kmh-speed-limit','NSW state wide 90km/h speed limit ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/90km_sign.jpg\" alt=\"90 km/h speed limit\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">NSW NRMA’s regional director Graham Blight recently told the media that the RTA’s hidden agenda is to drop the state-wide speed limit to 90km/h. The RTA said the lower limit was a benefit to all road users. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/50781/nsw-state-wide-speed-limit-90kmh/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/15/nsw-state-wide-90kmh-speed-limit/','2010-01-15 01:02:28','2010-01-15 01:02:28',NULL),(1798,'Crashzone - how to add images to the quote','crashzone-how-to-add-images-to-the-quote-3','Crashzone - how to add images to the quote','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-adding-images-3.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - adding images to the quote\" />\r\n\r\nAdding images to your quote is done by email\r\n\r\n* Open a new email\r\n* Type in you Crashzone email address\r\n* Type the Crashzone quote number into the subject i.e ( 5013 )\r\n* Attach images to the email\r\n* Send email\r\n* Images will now attach to the quote  ( the process takes approx 1 minute )\r\n* Click on the details tab to refresh the system and load the new images\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-images-on-details-page.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - images on details page\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/18/crashzone-how-to-add-images-to-the-quote-3/','2010-01-18 08:10:44','2010-01-18 08:10:44',NULL),(1799,'How to add a 2nd colour in the paint section ','how-to-add-a-2nd-colour-in-the-paint-section','How to add a 2nd colour in the paint section ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/crashzone-2nd-colour-on-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone 2nd colour on quote\" />\r\n\r\n* From the picklist select miscellaneous and then click on \"2nd colour\"\r\n* This will add a new line to the quote \"2nd colour\"\r\n* Add your 2nd colour items to the quote\r\n* fill in the 2nd colour rate in the rate box\r\n* Add the hour figure for the paint item\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/crashzone-2nd-colour-rate.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone 2nd colour rate shown on quote\" />\r\n\r\n* On the viewed quote the rate for the 2nd colour is shown in the description.\r\n<p align=\"left\">If you have any questions or need help with adding a 2nd colour please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/19/how-to-add-a-2nd-colour-in-the-paint-section/','2010-01-19 07:39:46','2010-01-19 07:39:46',NULL),(1803,'Harbourtown Smash Repairs -  Labrador repairer','harbourtown-smash-repairs-labrador-repairer','Harbourtown Smash Repairs -  Labrador repairer',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/harbourtownsmash-repairs.jpg\" alt=\"Harbourtown Smash Repairs\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Harbourtown Smash Repairs </strong>\r\n\r\n1/8 Gibbs St Labrador QLD 4214\r\nPh: 07 55376188\r\nFax: 07 55376100\r\nEmail: harbourtownsmash@bigpond.com\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/harbourtownsmash-repairs-map.jpg\" alt=\"Harbourtown Smash Repairs map\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/20/harbourtown-smash-repairs-labrador-repairer/','2010-01-20 06:12:26','2010-01-20 06:12:26',NULL),(1806,'Crashzone - how to create a supplement quote','crashzone-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-2','Crashzone - how to create a supplement quote','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-create-new-supplement-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement quote\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-new-supplement-button.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement button\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"> To create a new supplement click on the drop down box in the quote page and select new. This will generate a blank supplement, in this example quote 5002.1</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-items.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement items\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Write the supplement quote and from the view page you can view the supplement quote and the original quote. When invoicing any supplements will be added to the original quote to give a grand total.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-quote-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement qutoe example\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/21/crashzone-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-2/','2010-01-21 05:27:30','2010-01-21 05:27:30',NULL),(1807,'Anti hoon laws to crush cars','anti-hoon-laws-to-crush-cars','Anti hoon laws to crush cars','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/anti-hoon-laws.jpg\" alt=\"Anti Hoon laws\" />\r\n\r\nThe proposal from the Victorian government where repeat offenders will have their cars crushed if a driver owns the car and has two previous offences for crimes such as exceeding the speed limit by 45km/h or more, drag racing, burnouts or dangerous driving. for the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/54268/victorian-state-government-to-crush-hoons-cars-at-3rd-offence/\">caradvice.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/25/anti-hoon-laws-to-crush-cars/','2010-01-25 02:32:27','2017-10-30 18:45:11',NULL),(1809,'Ford Falcon - front wheel drive','ford-falcon-front-wheel-drive','Ford Falcon - front wheel drive',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/fordfalcon.jpg\" alt=\"Ford Falcon\" />\r\n\r\nFord  Motor Company\'s global chief executive Alan Mulally last week confirmed the next  Falcon would end the nameplate\'s decades-long run as a model designed and  developed exclusively in Australia. It will instead be based on a new global  large-car platform, likely to be shared with the US market\'s Taurus, currently  a front-wheel-drive.  For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/ford-on-front-foot-20100125-mt2q.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/27/ford-falcon-front-wheel-drive/','2010-01-27 03:00:07','2010-01-27 03:00:07',NULL),(1812,'Mercedes Gullwing','mercedes-gullwing','Mercedes Gullwing',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/mercedes-gullwing.jpg\" alt=\"Mercedes Gullwing\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The new Mercedes-Benz Gullwing is powered by a 6.2-litre AMG V8 engine developing 420kW of power, making it the fastest Mercedes-Benz ever produced for the road. With a $500,000 price tag the first 30 Australians to order will take delivery in July. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/gullwing-production-begins-20100128-n0u5.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/01/29/mercedes-gullwing/','2010-01-29 04:52:22','2010-01-29 04:52:22',NULL),(1814,'The world\'s top 5 safest cars','the-worlds-top-5-safest-cars','The world\'s top 5 safest cars','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/vw-crash-test.jpg\" title=\"VW Golf safety crash\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/vw-crash-test.jpg\" alt=\"VW Golf safety crash\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Volkswagen Golf has come out on top in a list of the five safest cars of  2009, released by European independent crash test body, Euro<span style=\"background: yellow none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous\" class=\"J-JK9eJ-PJVNOc\"></span> NCAP. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/rated-the-worlds-top-five-safest-cars-20100129-n2en.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/01/the-worlds-top-5-safest-cars/','2010-02-01 01:22:08','2010-02-01 01:22:08',NULL),(1815,'Ferrari 599 - Hybrid ','ferrari-599-hybrid','Ferrari 599 - Hybrid ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/ferrari-599.jpg\" alt=\"Ferrari 599 Hybrid\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The 599 will retain its V12 powerplant, adding a version of the KERS (Kinetic Energy Recovery System) setup originally developed for F1. While not a hybrid in the ‘traditional’ sense, the combination will reportedly result in a 30 percent improvement to fuel economy. For the full story please visit the <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49256/ferrari-599-hybrid-to-land-at-geneva-motor-show/#title\">motorreport.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/02/ferrari-599-hybrid/','2010-02-02 07:24:05','2010-02-02 07:24:05',NULL),(1817,'Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-7','Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','\r\n<p class=\"entry\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Maintenance of your web browser may be required on occasion. By deleting temporary files and cookies it allows Crashzone to do a fresh reload next time you re start the system. Below is a quick guide on how to preform the maintenance on Internet Explorer and Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or further help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a> or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/04/web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-7/','2010-02-04 01:34:28','2010-02-04 01:34:28',NULL),(1818,'New Ferrari & Maserati dealership Sydney ','new-ferrari-maserati-dealership-sydney','New Ferrari & Maserati dealership Sydney ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/ferrari-and-maserati-showroom.jpg\" alt=\"Ferrari &amp; Maserati dealership Sydney\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The new $30 million Ferrari Maserati Sydney dealership was officially opened in Waterloo with two very special debut guest appearances – the Ferrari 458 Italia and the Maserati GranCabrio. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/55938/ferrari-458-italia-maserati-grancabrio-debut-at-new-ferrari-maserati-sydney-dealership/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/05/new-ferrari-maserati-dealership-sydney/','2010-02-05 06:02:04','2010-02-05 06:03:24',NULL),(1820,'Porsche 911 turbo S - fastest yet ','porsche-911-turbo-s-fastest-yet','Porsche 911 turbo S - fastest yet ',' <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/porsche-911-turbo-s.jpg\" title=\"Porsche 911 turbo S\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/porsche-911-turbo-s.jpg\" alt=\"Porsche 911 turbo S\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"left\"> The 911 Turbo S, completing the 0 to 100 km/h sprint in a V8 Supercar beating 3.3 seconds.The S, which will be available locally in coupe and cabriolet form from August, gets a tweaked version of the Turbo’s 3.8-litre flat six. Power is up from 368kW to 390kW, while torque jumps from 650Nm to 700Nm. Despite the extra performance, fuel consumption stays the same at 11.4 litres per 100km. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/fastest-porsche-yet-20100209-no3o.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/09/porsche-911-turbo-s-fastest-yet/','2010-02-09 07:50:35','2010-02-09 07:50:35',NULL),(1822,'Global recall for 2010 Toyota Prius','global-recall-for-2010-toyota-prius','Global recall for 2010 Toyota Prius',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/toyota-prius.jpg\" alt=\"Toyota Prius\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"> Toyota has today announced a global recall of the 2010 Toyota Prius. The recall affects 2378 Prius cars in Australia and around 400,000 globally. This issue is not a ‘failure’, as such, but an inconsistency in brake feel explaining that the complaints concerned the brake pedal going soft after ABS activation on some surfaces. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49654/49654/#title\">themotorreport.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/11/global-recall-for-2010-toyota-prius/','2010-02-11 03:04:19','2010-02-11 03:04:19',NULL),(1824,'Crashzone accounting - export data','crashzone-accounting-export-data-2','Crashzone accounting - export data','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/accounting2.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - accounting data export\" />\r\n\r\nHow to export your invoices and job data from Crashzone\r\n\r\n* Click on the settings link to access the settings page\r\n* Scroll down to the backup section in the settings page\r\n* Enter the  quote range for the export ( quote number “From” “To” )\r\n* Click on “CSV” to generate the file\r\n* You will receive an email  with a link to download\r\n* Download  the file from your email\r\n* Extract the ZIP file to your computer\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-csv.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone CSV data export\" />\r\n\r\n* Once extracted you will have 2 new files detail.csv and Invoic.csv\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-csv-files.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone CSV files\" />\r\n\r\n1/ <strong>Detail.csv</strong> is a list of all the data from your Crashzone system for the quote range selected\r\n\r\n2/ <strong>Invoice.csv</strong> is a list of all invoices in the quote range selected\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-invoice-report-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone invoice report example ( data export function )\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with exporting your data please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/15/crashzone-accounting-export-data-2/','2010-02-15 05:47:13','2010-02-15 05:47:13',NULL),(1825,'Volvo S60 stops for pedestrians','volvo-s60-stops-for-pedestrians','Volvo S60 stops for pedestrians',' <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/volvo-s60.jpg\" title=\"Volvo S60\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/volvo-s60.jpg\" alt=\"Volvo S60\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"left\">The new S60 is the first car in the world with a system to see pedestrians and brake automatically if there is an chance of a collision. On the safety front, and in addition to the pedestrian-protection system, Volvo is fitting a more-advanced ESP stability system that detects skidding earlier, the City Safety system which brakes automatically to avoid car to car collisions introduced on the XC60 and a new corner traction control system. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.carsguide.com.au/site/news-and-reviews/car-news/volvo_s60_can_see_pedestrians\">carsguide.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/17/volvo-s60-stops-for-pedestrians/','2010-02-17 01:58:39','2010-02-17 01:58:39',NULL),(1827,'Car emissions lowered in Australia','car-emissions-lowered-in-australia','Car emissions lowered in Australia',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/old-exhaust-mufflers.jpg\" alt=\"old exhaust mufflers\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">New figures released by the Federal Chamber of Automotive Industries this week show that car emissions in Australia have reached a record low. The FCAI had set a target of reducing CO2 emissions from an average 252.4g/km in 2002 to 222g/km by the end of 2010 which has now been exceeded. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49851/vehicle-emissions-reach-record-low-in-australia\">themotorreport.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/18/car-emissions-lowered-in-australia/','2010-02-18 08:28:05','2010-02-18 08:28:05',NULL),(1829,'Smart Car Vs Mercedes - crash test','smart-car-vs-mercedes-crash-test','Smart Car Vs Mercedes - crash test','<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/he6TL15pJtw&hl=en_US&fs=1&\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/he6TL15pJtw&hl=en_US&fs=1&\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\"></embed></object>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/19/smart-car-vs-mercedes-crash-test/','2010-02-19 07:05:08','2010-02-19 07:05:08',NULL),(1831,'Red light speeding cameras rolled out in NSW','red-light-speeding-cameras-rolled-out-in-nsw','Red light speeding cameras rolled out in NSW','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/speed-camera.jpg\" alt=\"Speed Camera\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Motorist risk losing all 12 demerit points from their driver\'s licence in one hit from new super traffic cameras being rolled out across NSW. The digital cameras, which can detect speeding and red-light-running offences at the same time, can penalise drivers twice. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://smh.drive.com.au/motor-news/red-alert-lights-camera-takes-your-licence-in-one-go-20100220-ompu.html\">smh.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/22/red-light-speeding-cameras-rolled-out-in-nsw/','2010-02-22 04:21:01','2010-02-22 04:21:01',NULL),(1832,'Carlsson C25','carlsson-c25','Carlsson C25',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/carlsson-c25.jpg\" alt=\"Carlsson C25\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The C25 is based on the not-slow Mercedes-Benz SL65 AMG Black  pumping out 554kW of power and limited to 1150Nm of torque. One hundred kilometres an hour in just 3.7 seconds. A top speed of 352km/h. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/quick-silver-20100219-olte.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/23/carlsson-c25/','2010-02-23 07:31:24','2010-02-23 07:31:24',NULL),(1835,'The risk of electric shock ','the-risk-of-electric-shock','The risk of electric shock ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/electric-car.jpg\" alt=\"Electric Car\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Risk of electric shock and possible injury or death to repairers of electric vehicles has prompted VACC to call for industry-wide consultation on electric vehicles (EVs) and hybrids. VACC is calling on the State and Federal Government to act to address standards, industry training needs and licensing for the service and repair of these vehicles. For the full story please visit the <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49881/call-for-consultation-on-risks-to-repairers-of-electric-vehicles\">motorreport.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/02/25/the-risk-of-electric-shock/','2010-02-25 00:35:47','2010-02-25 00:35:47',NULL),(1838,'8.5 million Toyota vehicles recalled','85-million-toyota-vehicles-recalled','8.5 million Toyota vehicles recalled','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/mr-toyoda.jpg\" alt=\"Toyota president Akio Toyoda\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal\">Toyota president Akio Toyoda has formally apologised for the deadly auto defects that have driven the world\'s top carmaker into crisis.</strong><strong> </strong>About 8.5 million Toyota vehicles have been recalled due to issues with sudden unintended acceleration. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/business/breaking-news/toyota-chief-deeply-sorry-for-car-defects/story-e6frfkur-1225834129906\">news.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/01/85-million-toyota-vehicles-recalled/','2010-03-01 01:04:43','2010-03-01 01:04:43',NULL),(1840,'Koenigsegg Agera','koenigsegg-agera','Koenigsegg Agera',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/koenigsegg-agera.jpg\" alt=\"Koenigsegg Agera\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">With a carbon-fibre, kevlar and aluminium honeycomb body weighing in at just 1284kg, the Agera will rocket to 100km/h in 3.1 seconds. Power comes from a 4.7 litre twin turbo V8 pumping out 680KW and 1100NM of torque. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49911/2011-koenigsegg-agera-revealed-ahead-of-geneva-debut-this-week\">themotorreport.com.au</a><br clear=\"all\" /></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/02/koenigsegg-agera/','2010-03-02 02:49:29','2010-03-02 02:49:29',NULL),(1842,'Victoria to ban trucks from the right lane ','victoria-to-ban-trucks-from-the-right-lane','Victoria to ban trucks from the right lane ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/truck.jpg\" alt=\"Truck on Freeway\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">In a bid to improve road saftey trucks will be banned from the right hand lane on Victoria\'s multi lane freeways. The restrictions will apply to all heavy vehicles with a Gross Vehicle Mass over 4.5 tonnes. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49928/new-law-bans-trucks-from-right-hand-lane-on-victorian-freeways\">themotorreport.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/04/victoria-to-ban-trucks-from-the-right-lane/','2010-03-04 02:49:10','2010-03-04 02:49:10',NULL),(1843,'Crashzone - Queensland','crashzone-queensland-3','Crashzone - Queensland','\r\n<p align=\"left\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/10/map.JPG\" alt=\"Crashzone in QLD\" /></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"> Crashzone will be visiting repairers in the Brisbane and Gold Coast area from the 9th of March to the 16th of March. If you would like a demonstration or some one on one training during this period please contact  <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\">support@crashzone.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/05/crashzone-queensland-3/','2010-03-05 02:29:24','2010-03-05 02:29:24',NULL),(1844,'Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-8','Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','\r\n<p align=\"left\">Maintenance of your web browser may be required on occasion. By deleting temporary files and cookies it allows Crashzone to do a fresh reload next time you re start the system. Below is a quick guide on how to preform the maintenance on Internet Explorer and Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or further help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a> or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/10/web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-8/','2010-03-10 03:01:01','2010-03-10 03:01:01',NULL),(1846,'Queensland considering .0.2 blood alcohol limit','queensland-considering-02-blood-alcohol-limit','Queensland considering .0.2 blood alcohol limit','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/police-breath-testing.jpg\" alt=\"Police breath testing\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Queensland government is considering lowering the state\'s legal blood alcohol limit for motorists to .02. Two countries to have already established a .02 blood-alcohol limit are Norway and Sweden. Both nations have the lowest road toll rates in the world. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.themotorreport.com.au/49997/queensland-considering-lowering-drink-driving-limit-to-02\">themotorreport.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/15/queensland-considering-02-blood-alcohol-limit/','2010-03-15 01:40:24','2010-03-15 01:40:24',NULL),(1848,'Free gun with every Hummer Sold','free-gun-with-every-hummer-sold','Free gun with every Hummer Sold','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hummer-and-free-gun.jpg\" alt=\"Hummer &amp; Free Gun\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">In the US a Missouri car dealership offering a free shotgun with every new Hummer sold. Following the recent slow down in GM sales, the dealership decided to sell guns in the same showroom as its cars. It seems it didn’t take long to put two-and-two together. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/61137/us-dealer-offers-free-shotgun-with-every-hummer-sold/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/17/free-gun-with-every-hummer-sold/','2010-03-17 01:38:46','2010-03-17 01:38:46',NULL),(1849,'Faster internet','faster-internet-2','Faster internet','<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/slow-internet.jpg\" alt=\"Slow internet\" />\r\nAre you paying top dollar for old technology Internet ?\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\">Many Australian businesses use Telstra bigpond as their  Internet provider. In the past there was not a lot of choices and  Telstra was the main player when it came to your Internet connection.   The problem is that the nature of the Internet has changed and your  average business requires faster Internet and larger download limits  than before. Many customers are still stuck with ADSL1 connections that  are many times slower than your basic ADSL2 connection.  Telstra do  offer the newer and faster ADSL2 connections but usually the price is no  where as competitive as the other major providers. Two ISP that  offer ADSL2 and provide fast and reliable Internet are iinet and TPG.\r\nTo test your Internet speed visit <a href=\"http://www.zdnet.com.au/broadband/speedtest.htm\">http://www.zdnet.com.au/broadband/speedtest.htm</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.iinet.net.au/customers/\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/iinet2.jpg\" alt=\"iinet\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.tpg.com.au/\" title=\"TPG\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/tpg4.jpg\" alt=\"TPG\" style=\"width: 108px; height: 58px\" height=\"59\" width=\"112\" /></a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/22/faster-internet-2/','2010-03-22 00:39:43','2010-03-22 00:39:44',NULL),(1850,'Ferrari world Abu Dhabi','ferrari-world-abu-dhabi','Ferrari world Abu Dhabi',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ferrari-world.jpg\" alt=\"Ferrari World\" />\r\n\r\nCovering more than 100,000 square metres, Ferrari World Abu Dhabi  will be the world’s largest indoor park with a huge number of high  octane attractions. Set to open later this year the highlight is a new roller coaster which will be the fastest in  the  world – travelling at more than 200km/h to simulate the feeling of  being behind the wheel of a Ferrari Formula 1 car. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/61877/ferrari-world-abu-dhabi-preview-opens-2010/\">caradvice.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/23/ferrari-world-abu-dhabi/','2010-03-23 02:09:40','2010-03-23 02:09:40',NULL),(1854,'Made You Look Kustoms - Arundel repairer','made-you-look-kustoms-arundle-repairer','Made You Look Kustoms - Arundel repairer','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/made-you-look-kustoms.jpg\" alt=\"Made You Look Kustoms\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Made You Look Kustoms</strong>\r\n\r\n<span id=\"ctl03_repMain_ctl02_CompanyAddress\">1/10 Ivan St Arundel Gold Coast QLD 4214</span>\r\nPh: <span id=\"ctl03_repMain_ctl02_CompanyAddress\"></span><span id=\"ctl03_repMain_ctl02_CompanyAddress\">07 5528 8333</span>\r\nFax: 07 5528 8333\r\nEmail: madeyoulookkustoms@bigpond.com\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/made-you-look-kustoms-map.jpg\" alt=\"Made You Look Kustoms map\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/24/made-you-look-kustoms-arundle-repairer/','2010-03-24 05:56:02','2010-03-24 05:57:17',NULL),(1856,'Tata Nano Prone to catching fire','tata-nano-prone-to-catching-fire','Tata Nano Prone to catching fire','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/tata-nano.jpg\" alt=\"Tata Nano\" />\r\n\r\nThe world’s cheapest new car is fast earning a reputation for being a  really hot hatch. But the latest plight of the Nano has  nothing to do with speed or performance, but a reported propensity to  catch fire. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/budget-car-becomes-3000-bbq-20100324-quri.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/25/tata-nano-prone-to-catching-fire/','2010-03-25 06:06:41','2010-03-25 06:06:41',NULL),(1860,'Claims top 100 million dollars in Perth storms','claims-top-100-million-dollars-in-perth-storms','Claims top 100 million dollars in Perth storms','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/wa-storm-1.jpg\" alt=\"Perth storm WA\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/wa-storm2.jpg\" alt=\"Perth storm WA\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/wa-storm3.jpg\" alt=\"Perth storm WA\" />\r\n\r\nAn Insurance Council of Australia spokeswoman said 23,000 claims  totalling $108 million had been made so far. The Council has declared  the storms a \"general insurance catastrophe\". More than 158,000 houses were left without power at the height of the  storm. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.watoday.com.au/wa-news/insurance-companies-declare-catastrophe-as-claims-top-100-million-20100324-qux6.html?autostart=1\">watoday.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/26/claims-top-100-million-dollars-in-perth-storms/','2010-03-26 01:55:02','2010-03-26 01:55:02',NULL),(1866,'Audi Australia the Lighthouse','audi-australia-the-lighthouse','Audi Australia the Lighthouse','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/audi1.jpg\" alt=\"Audi Australia the Lighthouse\" />\r\n\r\nThe eight-level, 16000+ square metre facility located at Victoria Park  was built in less than 12 months at a cost of 51 million dollars\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/audi5.jpg\" alt=\"Audi Australia the Lighthouse\" />\r\n\r\nMore new cars on level 2\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/audi3.jpg\" alt=\"Audi R8 V10\" />\r\n\r\nAudi R8 V10 5.2 FSI Quattro\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/audi2.jpg\" alt=\"Audi Australia the Lighthouse - work shop\" />\r\n\r\n21 mechanical work bays\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/audi4.jpg\" alt=\"Audi Australia the Lighthouse - workshop bench\" />\r\n\r\nEach work bay has it\'s own fully contained work bench.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/29/audi-australia-the-lighthouse/','2010-03-29 06:40:18','2010-03-29 06:40:18',NULL),(1868,'Hennessey Venom GT 1200hp','hennessey-venom-gt-1200hp','Hennessey Venom GT 1200hp','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/venom-gt.jpg\" alt=\"Venom GT\" />\r\n\r\nA $1 million-plus supercar described as a “weapon of mass propulsion”  that’s twice as powerful as a Lamborghini and can reach four times the  speed limit could be on its way to Australia. The Hennessey Venom GT is,  in essence, a British-made  Lotus Elise with a stretched body that’s fitted with an all-American  6.2-litre Chevrolet supercharged V8 engine. For the full story please  visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/420kmh-car-could-come-to-australia-20100330-rary.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/03/31/hennessey-venom-gt-1200hp/','2010-03-31 05:36:26','2010-03-31 05:36:26',NULL),(1869,'Workflow Computing - Motion tablet PC','workflow-computing-motion-tablet-pc-4','Workflow Computing - Motion tablet PC','<a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/Smash-Repairs-s/65.htm\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/workflow-computing.jpg\" alt=\"Workflow Computing\" /></a>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"></span>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\">Motion Computing Tablet PC\'s will work out of the box with the majority of smash repair quoting software applications including Crashzone, Auto-quote, QuotePlus, VQS, Flexiquote etc. Instead of using paper, pen and clipboard plus a separate digital camera for quoting, it is now possible to replace these with single device.\r\nSo for a Tablet PC Solution for your Smash Repair Business, contact Workflow Computing, Australia\'s Motion Computing Specialist, today on (02) 9029-8056. <a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/\">www.workflowcomputing.com.au</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.workflowcomputing.com.au/Smash-Repairs-s/65.htm\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/rohan-from-workflow-computing.jpg\" alt=\"Rohan from Workflow Computing\" /></a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/06/workflow-computing-motion-tablet-pc-4/','2010-04-06 02:38:21','2010-04-06 02:38:21',NULL),(1870,'Crashzone page setup for printing','crashzone-page-setup-for-printing-2','Crashzone page setup for printing','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-header-and-footer.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone header and footer - when printing the quote\" />\r\n\r\nTo remove the header and footer text when printing your Crashzone  quote\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-page-setup-in-ie.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone page setup in Internet Explorer\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>From internet Explorer</strong>\r\n\r\n* Click on file ( top left corner )\r\n* Click on page Setup\r\n* Delete all the text from the Header field\r\n* Delete all the text from the Footer field\r\n* Click OK to save the changes\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-page-setup-in-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone page setup in Firefox\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>From Firefox</strong>\r\n\r\n* Click on File ( top left corner )\r\n* Click on Page Setup\r\n* Click on Margins &amp; Header/Footer tab\r\n* Change all the drop down boxes to –blank–\r\n* Click OK to save the changes\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-printed-quote.jpg\" title=\"Crashzone printed quote example\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-printed-quote.thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone printed quote example\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with your page setup please  contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/08/crashzone-page-setup-for-printing-2/','2010-04-08 02:48:36','2010-04-08 02:48:36',NULL),(1871,'5 million Toyota\'s sold in Australia','5-million-toyotas-sold-in-australia','5 million Toyota\'s sold in Australia','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/toyota-assembly-line.jpg\" alt=\"Toyota assembly line\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"><font color=\"black\" face=\"verdana\" size=\"2\">While the first one  million sales took more than 20 years, it was just nine years for the  second  million, eight for the third million, under six years for the fourth  million and less than five years for  the most recent milestone. The most popular Toyota  over the past 47 years has been Corolla with 1.1 million sales,  representing  more than one in five Toyotas sold here. The Corolla was built in  Australia from 1968 to 1999, with more  than 600,000 units coming off the Melbourne production line. For the  full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.nextcar.com.au/n.toyota.2010.5mil.10apr.html\">nextcar.com.au</a></font></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/09/5-million-toyotas-sold-in-australia/','2010-04-09 02:33:19','2010-04-09 02:33:19',NULL),(1874,'New repairable write-off legislation for NSW','new-repairable-write-off-legislation-for-nsw','New repairable write-off legislation for NSW','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/honda-crv-rollover.jpg\" alt=\"Honda CRV write-off\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The NSW government announces new legislation to ban the re-registration  of all repairable written-off  vehicles. It’s estimated that as many as six out of ten of the 20,537 repairable  written-off vehicles presented for re-registration in 2009 posed serious  questions about the origin of the parts used to repair them. It is hoped the new legislation, which is due to be implemented from  August this year, will help stop the sale of potentially unsafe vehicles  to unsuspecting customers. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/64435/nsw-government-to-introduce-new-repairable-write-off-legislation/\">caradvice.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/12/new-repairable-write-off-legislation-for-nsw/','2010-04-12 02:38:29','2010-04-12 02:38:29',NULL),(1875,'How to update hourly rates in Crashzone ','how-to-update-hourly-rates-in-crashzone','How to update hourly rates in Crashzone ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/crashzone-rates-on-quote1.jpg\" alt=\"How to update hourly rates in Crashzone\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>To update the hourly rates on an adjusted quote:</strong>\r\n\r\n* From the details page go the rates box\r\n* Enter the new hourly rates in the R&amp;R, Repair &amp; Paint fields\r\n* Click on the update quote button\r\n* The quote will now re calculate all labour items with the new rates\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/crashzone-rates-changed-on-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone rates changed on quote\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/14/how-to-update-hourly-rates-in-crashzone/','2010-04-14 04:09:03','2010-04-14 04:09:03',NULL),(1879,'Airbags go off in Mercedes','airbags-go-off-in-mercedes','Airbags go off in Mercedes','<object width=\"480\" height=\"385\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/lmbW55-zQFw&hl=en_US&fs=1&\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/lmbW55-zQFw&hl=en_US&fs=1&\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"480\" height=\"385\"></embed></object>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/16/airbags-go-off-in-mercedes/','2010-04-16 03:30:46','2010-04-16 03:30:46',NULL),(1880,'Crashzone accounting - export data','crashzone-accounting-export-data-3','Crashzone accounting - export data','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/accounting2.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - accounting data export\" />\r\n\r\nHow to export your invoices and job data from Crashzone\r\n\r\n* Click on the settings link to access the settings page\r\n* Scroll down to the backup section in the settings page\r\n* Enter the  quote range for the export ( quote number “From” “To” )\r\n* Click on “CSV” to generate the file\r\n* You will receive an email  with a link to download\r\n* Download  the file from your email\r\n* Extract the ZIP file to your computer\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-csv.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone CSV data export\" />\r\n\r\n* Once extracted you will have 2 new files detail.csv and Invoic.csv\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-csv-files.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone CSV files\" />\r\n\r\n1/ <strong>Detail.csv</strong> is a list of all the data from your  Crashzone system for the quote range selected\r\n\r\n2/ <strong>Invoice.csv</strong> is a list of all invoices in the  quote range selected\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-invoice-report-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone invoice report example ( data export function )\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with exporting your data  please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/19/crashzone-accounting-export-data-3/','2010-04-19 02:59:52','2010-04-19 02:59:52',NULL),(1881,'Digital camera image size','digital-camera-image-size-4','Digital camera image size','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-image-size.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone image size setting on digital camera\" />\r\n\r\nWith most digital point-and-shoot cameras, you can actually choose a  lower resolution than the camera’s advertised maximum, which is where  it’s set when you take it out of the box. You do this by entering the  shooting menu and selecting the “Image Size” or “Resolution” option.  When you do that, you’ll see a series of number pairs such as these:\r\n\r\n* 3648 x 2736 or 10 megapixel ( 1.1 MB to 2.2 MB approx)\r\n* 3264 x 2448 or 8 megapixel ( 970 KB to 1.9 MB approx )\r\n* 2048 x 1536  or 3.1 megapixel ( 500 KB to 1 MB approx )\r\n* 1600 x 1200 or 1.9 megapixel ( 250 KB to 700KB approx )\r\n* 1280 x 960 or 1.2 megapixel ( 240 KB to 490 KB approx )\r\n* 1024 x 768 or 0.8 megapixel ( 170 KB to 350 KB approx )\r\n<strong>* 640 x 480 or VGA ( 75 KB to 150 KB approx )   - ORM, PNET,  ARNIE setting\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nSetting a lower resolution level creates a smaller-sized picture  file. When you adjust the resolution downward, you’ll see the little  number on the viewing screen and/or LCD panel that tells you how many  more pictures you can fit on the card go up and up. Set 640 x 480, and  you’ll be able to fit hundreds if not thousands of pictures on a  decent-sized memory card.\r\n\r\nWhen emailing images a lower/lowest setting on your camera is always  best this will allow you send  images quickly and make it easier for  your customer to download and store the images you send to them.\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with setting up your camera  please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/21/digital-camera-image-size-4/','2010-04-21 02:28:52','2010-04-21 02:28:52',NULL),(1882,'New speed camera can book you from outer space','new-speed-camera-can-book-you-from-outer-space','New speed camera can book you from outer space',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/satellite.jpg\" alt=\"camera can book you from outer space\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Known as ‘SpeedSpike’, the system uses satellites to measure the average  speed of a vehicle between two points. The satellite-mounted cameras  have advanced number plate reading technology which is coupled to a  global positioning system (GPS) receiver. For the full story please  visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/65608/new-speed-cameras-on-trial-in-uk-can-book-drivers-from-space/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/27/new-speed-camera-can-book-you-from-outer-space/','2010-04-27 01:28:34','2010-04-27 01:28:34',NULL),(1886,'West Burleigh Smash Repairs - Burleigh heads repairer','west-burleigh-smash-repairs-burleigh-heads-repairer','West Burleigh Smash Repairs - Burleigh heads repairer','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/west-burlrigh-smash-repairs.jpg\" alt=\"WEST BURLEIGH SMASH REPAIRS\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>West Burleigh Smash Repairs</strong>\r\n39 West Burleigh Road Burleigh Heads QLD 4220\r\nPh: 07 5535 6698\r\nFax: 07 5535 2199\r\nEmail: westburleighsmash@hotmail.com\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/west-burlrigh-smash-repairs-map.jpg\" alt=\"WEST BURLEIGH SMASH REPAIRS map\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/04/29/west-burleigh-smash-repairs-burleigh-heads-repairer/','2010-04-29 02:08:29','2010-04-29 02:08:29',NULL),(1888,'Audi R8 GT','audi-r8-gt','Audi R8 GT','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/audi-r8-gt.jpg\" alt=\"Audi R8 GT\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The track focused Audi R8 GT is more powerful, lighter and faster  than the standard R8 V10, with only 333 examples to be made each  carrying its production number on the shift lever knob.The 5.2-litre V10 engine has been modified to produce additional 26kW  and 10Nm, bringing its peak output to 412kW and 540Nm with the rush  continuing all the way to redline at 8,700rpm. For the full story please  visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/66423/2011-audi-r8-gt-performance-flagship-unveiled/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/05/03/audi-r8-gt/','2010-05-03 02:13:05','2010-05-03 02:13:05',NULL),(1889,'Crashzone works with ORM 3.0 for FREE','crashzone-works-with-orm-30-for-free','Crashzone works with ORM 3.0 for FREE',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/hsv-gts-e2.jpg\" alt=\"HSV GTS E2\" />\r\n\r\nAs of 30 April 2010 the old ORM communication process, commonly known as QDE 2.6, has been decommissioned. ORM will now only communicate with repairers that are using the new QDE 3.0 standard. Good news is that Crashzone uses QDE 3.0 and you can be up and running with ORM today for free. Please contact support@crashzone.com.au for further information or help to setting up ORM.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.c