ET and  ORM.  For more information please contact  support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/05/21/crashzone-update-scheduled-for-the-24052010/','2010-05-21 07:53:20','2010-05-21 07:53:20',NULL),(1908,'Crashzone - system maintenance','crashzone-system-maintenance-2','Crashzone - system maintenance','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/04/sm.jpg\" alt=\"sm.jpg\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong>\r\n<p align=\"left\"> The Crashzone website maybe offline today from 7pm (EST)  to 8pm (EST) Monday the 24 of May. The down time is necessary to  preform scheduled maintenance. During this time Crashzone maybe  inaccessible. We apologise for any inconvenience and appreciate your  understanding. If you have any questions or concerns in relation to this  notice please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\">support@crashzone.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/05/24/crashzone-system-maintenance-2/','2010-05-24 11:01:26','2010-05-24 11:01:26',NULL),(1909,'Crashzone update complete','crashzone-update-complete','Crashzone update complete','\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">An update has been made to the Crashzone to improve the system and add new features. By deleting temporary files and cookies it allows Crashzone to  do a fresh reload on your computer next time you re start the system. Below is a quick  guide on how to preform the maintenance on Internet Explorer and  Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or further help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a>  or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/05/25/crashzone-update-complete/','2010-05-25 01:44:30','2010-05-25 01:44:30',NULL),(1911,'Crashzone works on Apple iPad','crashzone-works-on-apple-ipad','Crashzone works on Apple iPad','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/apple-ipad.jpg\" alt=\"Apple iPad works on Crashzone\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/05/28/crashzone-works-on-apple-ipad/','2010-05-28 03:37:34','2010-05-28 03:37:34',NULL),(1913,'First Smash repairer quoting with an Apple iPad ','first-smash-repairer-quoting-with-an-apple-ipad','First Smash repairer quoting with an Apple iPad ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/cz-using-ipad1.jpg\" alt=\"Apple iPad using Crashzone\" />\r\n\r\nJohn Hunter car repairs doing the first quote on an Apple iPad.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/05/31/first-smash-repairer-quoting-with-an-apple-ipad/','2010-05-31 05:07:15','2010-05-31 05:07:15',NULL),(1915,'Film your own car crash ','film-your-own-car-crash','Film your own car crash ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/car-smash1.jpg\" alt=\"Car accident\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">An internal G-Force sensor anticipates an impact and triggers a digital   video recorder to capture events surrounding a crash. The  device, has two cameras; one that points out  of the car and another  that films the cabin. It also records data,  including GPS location and speed of  the car. The makers say it can help  to determine who is at fault in an accident.   For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/film-your-own-car-crash-20100608-xrkt.html\">drive.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/08/film-your-own-car-crash/','2010-06-08 10:00:55','2010-06-08 10:02:07',NULL),(1916,'Crashzone new feature - email address in notes','crashzone-new-feature-email-address-in-notes','Crashzone new feature - email address in notes',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/crashzone-email-address-in-notes1.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone email address in the notes\" />\r\n\r\n* Note created in the details page\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/crashzone-email-address-in-notes.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone email address in the notes\" />\r\n\r\nWhen you email a quote, invoice or parts sheet from Crashzone a new note will be created in the details page showing the sent to email address with a time and date stamp. A copy of what has been sent is also attached in the notes.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/15/crashzone-new-feature-email-address-in-notes/','2010-06-15 02:57:23','2010-06-15 02:57:23',NULL),(1919,'iPad replaces owner\'s manual ','ipad-replaces-owners-manual','iPad replaces owner\'s manual ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/hyundai-equus.jpg\" alt=\"Hyundai Equus\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The humble car owner\'s manual looks like it\'s heading the way of the  Dodo, with  Hyundai instead issuing Apple iPads to owners of its new  premium sedan in the  United States. The iPad manual will incorporate   interactive text, pictures and  instructional videos to provide better assistance  to owners. For the  full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/ipad-replaces-owners-manual-20100616-yfjw.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/17/ipad-replaces-owners-manual/','2010-06-17 06:50:25','2010-06-17 06:50:25',NULL),(1922,'Crashzone new feature - select images for email','crashzone-new-feature-select-images-for-email','Crashzone new feature - select images for email','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/crashzone-select-images.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone select images\" />\r\n\r\nWhen emailing a quote to the customer or insurance company you can choose to either send all images or select individual images\r\n* From the view page tick \"Select Images\"\r\n* Enter the sending email address in the address bar\r\n* Click on Send\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/crashzone-highlight-images.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone highlight images to send\" />\r\n\r\n* All images are shown on the page\r\n* Click on the images that you want to send with the quote\r\n* Selected images are highlighted with a red border\r\n* Click on submit to send the quote and images\r\n* Once sent a confirmation note will be added in the Details page',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/18/crashzone-new-feature-select-images-for-email/','2010-06-18 05:26:23','2010-06-18 05:26:23',NULL),(1924,'Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-9','Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies','\r\n<p align=\"left\">Maintenance of your web browser may be required on  occasion. By deleting temporary files and cookies it allows Crashzone to  do a fresh reload next time you re start the system. Below is a quick  guide on how to preform the maintenance on Internet Explorer and  Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or further help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/22/web-browser-delete-temporary-files-and-cookies-9/','2010-06-22 02:15:31','2010-06-22 02:15:31',NULL),(1927,'Crashzone new feature - claim No. in subject when emailing ','crashzone-new-feature-claim-no-in-subject-when-emailing','Crashzone new feature - claim No. in subject when emailing ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/cz-claim-no.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone claim No. in subject of email by defauly\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">*When emailing a quote from the view page, Crashzone now adds in the claim number by default</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/cz-claim-number-details-page1.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone claim No. in the details page\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">*The claim number is taken from the details page in the insurance section</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/cz-edit-email.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone edit email subject and body\" />\r\n*The email subject and body can be altered by clicking on the edit button in view page',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/23/crashzone-new-feature-claim-no-in-subject-when-emailing/','2010-06-23 05:56:07','2010-06-23 05:56:07',NULL),(1934,'Crashzone works with ORM 3.0 for FREE','crashzone-works-with-orm-30-for-free-2','Crashzone works with ORM 3.0 for FREE','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/hsv-gts-e2.jpg\" alt=\"HSV GTS E2\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">As of 30 April 2010 the old ORM communication process, commonly known  as QDE 2.6, has been decommissioned. ORM will now only communicate with  repairers that are using the new QDE 3.0 standard. Good news is that  Crashzone uses QDE 3.0 and you can be up and running with ORM today for  free. Please contact support@crashzone.com.au for further information or  help to setting up ORM.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/24/crashzone-works-with-orm-30-for-free-2/','2010-06-24 09:33:18','2010-06-24 09:33:18',NULL),(1936,'Toyota Supra FT-HS','toyota-supra-ft-hs','Toyota Supra FT-HS',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/toyota_ft-hs-supra.jpg\" alt=\"Toyota Supra FT-HS\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Code-named the FT-HS, the Future Toyota Hybrid Sport development team has said they hope to release a new generation Toyota Supra to the public by 2013, and, they say it will achieve four-second 0-100km/h times using hybrid technology. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/71536/2013-toyota-supra-hybrid-production/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/25/toyota-supra-ft-hs/','2010-06-25 04:34:39','2010-06-25 04:34:39',NULL),(1938,'Electric cars not the answer','electric-cars-not-the-answer','Electric cars not the answer',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/honda-clarity.jpg\" alt=\"honda-clarity.jpg\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Honda in Europe, says fuel cell vehicles, which generate their own electricity on-board from a chemical reaction with hydrogen, are superior to electric vehicles and will be the “ultimate solution” to the industry’s energy needs. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/electric-cars-not-the-answer-honda-20100625-z4fr.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/29/electric-cars-not-the-answer/','2010-06-29 03:35:23','2010-06-29 03:35:23',NULL),(1940,'Terrafugia Transition flying car','terrafugia-transition-flying-car','Terrafugia Transition flying car',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/terrafugia-transition.jpg\" alt=\"Terrafugia Transition\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Transition needs just 520m to take off over an obstacle of 15m in height and can cruise at around 200km/h. It’ll also fly for a distance of about 700km before needing a refuel. The Transition only uses an average fuel consumption of 7.8L/100km on the road too, not bad for a car that absolutely flies. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/72324/terrafugia-transition-flying-car-passes-faa-regulations/\">cardavice.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/06/30/terrafugia-transition-flying-car/','2010-06-30 09:56:59','2010-06-30 09:56:59',NULL),(1942,'Crashzone accounting - export data','crashzone-accounting-export-data-4','Crashzone accounting - export data','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/accounting2.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - accounting data export\" />\r\n\r\nHow to export your invoices and job data from Crashzone\r\n\r\n* Click on the settings link to access the settings page\r\n* Scroll down to the backup section in the settings page\r\n* Enter the  quote range for the export ( quote number “From” “To” )\r\n* Click on “CSV” to generate the file\r\n* You will receive an email  with a link to download\r\n* Download  the file from your email\r\n* Extract the ZIP file to your computer\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-csv.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone CSV data export\" />\r\n\r\n* Once extracted you will have 2 new files detail.csv and Invoic.csv\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-csv-files.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone CSV files\" />\r\n\r\n1/ <strong>Detail.csv</strong> is a list of all the data from your   Crashzone system for the quote range selected\r\n\r\n2/ <strong>Invoice.csv</strong> is a list of all invoices in the   quote range selected\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-invoice-report-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone invoice report example ( data export function )\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with exporting your data   please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/01/crashzone-accounting-export-data-4/','2010-07-01 07:18:30','2010-07-01 07:18:30',NULL),(1944,'Happy Birthday Crashzone','happy-birthday-crashzone-2','Happy Birthday Crashzone','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/monaro.jpg\" alt=\"Monaro on the Nullarbor Plain\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Crashzone turns 3</strong>\r\n\r\nCrashzone has insurance integration with:\r\n<strong>* ORM\r\n* NTAR\r\n* PNET\r\n* ARNIE\r\n* ESTIMAGE</strong>\r\n\r\nCrashzone the first free web based quote system, 3 year on and it’s   still FREE.\r\nThanks to all our customers that have made Crashzone their No.1  preferred quoting system.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/05/happy-birthday-crashzone-2/','2010-07-05 04:55:44','2010-07-05 04:55:44',NULL),(1946,'3500HP Mini','3500hp-mini','3500HP Mini','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/mini-3500hp.jpg\" alt=\"Mini 3500HP\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">From the 2010 Goodwood Festival of Speed, a Mini fitted with a 11 tonne 3500bhp Cummins diesel engine.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/07/3500hp-mini/','2010-07-07 08:12:17','2010-07-07 08:12:17',NULL),(1949,'Platinum Auto Paints','platinum-auto-paints','Platinum Auto Paints','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/platinum-paints2.jpg\" alt=\"Platinum Auto Paints\" />\