peed camera Locations NSW','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/nsw-mobile-speed-camera.jpg\" alt=\"NSW mobile speed camera\" />\r\n\r\nThe white Ford  Territory’s, will be operated by a private government contractor rather  than a police officer meaning offenders will be unaware they have been  caught until a fine arrives in the mail. As though taking public safety out of the hands of the police wasn’t  controversial enough, the organisation behind these cameras is partly  owned by Macquarie Bank who has recognised the mobile speed camera  operation as a lucrative business opportunity  investing $275m to the  cause.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/mobile_speed_camera_locations_0710.pdf\" title=\"Mobile speed camera Locations NSW\">Mobile speed camera Locations NSW</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/22/mobile-speed-camera-locations-nsw/','2010-07-22 02:47:07','2010-07-22 02:47:07',NULL),(1964,'Crashzone - how to create a supplement quote','crashzone-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-3','Crashzone - how to create a supplement quote','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-create-new-supplement-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement quote\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-new-supplement-button.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement button\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"> To create a new supplement click on the drop down box  in the quote page and select new. This will generate a blank supplement,  in this example quote 5002.1</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-items.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement items\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Write the supplement quote and from the view page you  can view the supplement quote and the original quote. When invoicing any  supplements will be added to the original quote to give a grand total.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-quote-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement qutoe example\" />\r\n\r\n* Supplementary images are sent to the original quote\r\n* Use the select image function in the view page when emailing the supp quote\r\n\r\nFor further information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/26/crashzone-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-3/','2010-07-26 05:22:56','2010-07-26 05:22:56',NULL),(1966,'iPhone car key','iphone-car-key','iPhone car key',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/iphone-car-app.jpg\" alt=\"iPhone used as your car key\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">General Motors is working on an app for the iPhone and rival Google   phone for some of its cars sold in the United States. The phone  application  will allow drivers to activate all of the traditional key  fob features,  including unlocking the doors and opening the boot. There  will also be a  remote start function that could prove handy for  warming up the car on those  colder mornings (or cooling it down during  summer), and if you forget where you  parked you can set off your car\'s  horn and lights at the touch of a button so it  can alert you to its  location. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/the-iphone-car-key-20100727-10t8u.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/27/iphone-car-key/','2010-07-27 07:53:06','2010-07-27 07:53:06',NULL),(1967,'Crashzone update scheduled for the 29/07/2010','crashzone-update-scheduled-for-the-29072010','Crashzone update scheduled for the 29/07/2010','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2008/04/sm.jpg\" alt=\"sm.jpg\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Crashzone will make an update to the system taking effect from Thursday   the 29th of July approx 8pm Sydney time. The update will include general system fixes and improvements for ORM and PNET.  For more information  please contact  support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/29/crashzone-update-scheduled-for-the-29072010/','2010-07-29 04:11:05','2010-07-29 04:11:05',NULL),(1968,'Crashzone update complete','crashzone-update-complete-2','Crashzone update complete','\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">An update has been made to the Crashzone to improve the  system and add new features. By deleting temporary files and cookies it  allows Crashzone to  do a fresh reload on your computer next time you re  start the system. Below is a quick  guide on how to preform  the maintenance on Internet Explorer and  Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or further help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a>  or phone 1300 721 090</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/07/30/crashzone-update-complete-2/','2010-07-30 05:06:19','2010-07-30 05:06:19',NULL),(1970,'Bank holiday 02/08/2010','bank-holiday-02082010','Bank holiday 02/08/2010',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/tropical-retreat.jpg\" alt=\"Bank holiday\" />\r\n\r\nHappy bank holiday ( Panel Beaters Picnic )  to all the shop lucky enough to take a day off.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/02/bank-holiday-02082010/','2010-08-02 03:13:34','2010-08-02 03:13:34',NULL),(1971,'Crashzone - how to add images to the quote','crashzone-how-to-add-images-to-the-quote-5','Crashzone - how to add images to the quote','\r\n<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-adding-images-3.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - adding images to the quote\" /></p>\r\nAdding images to your quote is done by email\r\n\r\n* Open a new email\r\n* Type in your Crashzone email address\r\n* Type the Crashzone quote number into the subject i.e ( 5013 )\r\n* Attach images to the email\r\n* Send email\r\n* Images will now attach to the quote  ( the process takes approx 1  minute )\r\n* Click on the details tab to refresh the system and load the new images\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-images-on-details-page.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone - images on details page\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Please contact support@crashzone.com.au if you need any help with adding images to Crashzone</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/03/crashzone-how-to-add-images-to-the-quote-5/','2010-08-03 03:06:28','2010-08-03 03:06:28',NULL),(1973,'Three Apple iPad\'s on the workshop floor  ','three-apple-ipads-on-the-workshop-floor','Three Apple iPad\'s on the workshop floor  ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3-ipads.jpg\" alt=\"Three Apple iPads in use at John Hunter Car Repairs\" />\r\n\r\nThree Apple iPads in action at John Hunter Car Repairs',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/04/three-apple-ipads-on-the-workshop-floor/','2010-08-04 08:42:50','2010-08-04 08:42:50',NULL),(1974,'Crashzone - NTAR update','crashzone-ntar-update','Crashzone - NTAR update','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/spraybooth.jpg\" alt=\"Spray Booth\" />\r\n\r\nCrashzone has made an update to the system to include the latest changes made to <strong>NTAR</strong>. This includes the current times and schedule + the new paint material and consumable rates.\r\n\r\nS1 $17.51\r\nS2 $19.49\r\nM1 $21.13\r\nM2 $24.36\r\nM3 $27.74\r\nPaint consumables $5.92',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/06/crashzone-ntar-update/','2010-08-06 02:23:06','2010-08-06 02:23:06',NULL),(1977,'The worlds most expensive car - Bugatti Type 57SC Atlantic','the-worlds-most-expensive-car-bugatti-type-57sc-atlantic','The worlds most expensive car - Bugatti Type 57SC Atlantic','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1936-bugatti-type-57sc.jpg\" alt=\"Bugatti Type 57SC Atlantic\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">1937 Bugatti Type 57SC, only four of these cars were ever made and only two of them are said to still exist today.  It sold for US$30-40 million at auction recently. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/77056/1937-bugatti-type-57sc-atlantic-aka-worlds-most-expensive-car-is-on-display/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/09/the-worlds-most-expensive-car-bugatti-type-57sc-atlantic/','2010-08-09 03:46:40','2010-08-09 03:47:28',NULL),(1979,'Crashzone works on iPhone 4','crashzone-works-on-iphone-4','Crashzone works on iPhone 4','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/iphone-4-using-crashzone.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone running on iPhone 4\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/11/crashzone-works-on-iphone-4/','2010-08-11 04:23:16','2010-08-11 04:23:16',NULL),(1981,'Lamborghini sedan - Estoque','lamborghini-sedan-estoque','Lamborghini sedan - Estoque','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/lamborghini-sedan.jpg\" alt=\"Lamborghini sedan\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"> The Estoque powered by a 5.2-litre V10 capable of propelling the  aluminium-bodied four door to speeds in excess of 300km/h. The company  believes it could attract new customers with a four door  sports sedan that would rival the likes of the Porsche Panamera,  Maserati Quattroporte, Aston Martin Rapide and Ferrari 612 Scaglietti.  For the full story please visit<a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/lamborghini-sedan-back-in-business-20100812-120ai.html\"> drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/13/lamborghini-sedan-estoque/','2010-08-13 01:43:00','2010-08-13 01:43:00',NULL),(1982,'Sukuki SX4 Pikes Peak hill climb','sukuki-sx4-pikes-peak-hill-climb','Sukuki SX4 Pikes Peak hill climb','<object width=\"590\" height=\"385\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/G2y3OFf0ArU?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/G2y3OFf0ArU?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"590\" height=\"385\"></embed></object>\r\n\r\nSomething fun for Friday.\r\n669kW, 3.1-litre, twin-turbo V6 Suzuki SX4 attacking Pike Peak on a record run. ',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/20/sukuki-sx4-pikes-peak-hill-climb/','2010-08-20 04:14:01','2010-08-20 04:14:01',NULL),(1984,'New Ferrari 458 Vs tree','new-ferrari-458-vs-tree','New Ferrari 458 Vs tree','<object width=\"590\" height=\"385\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/iU5v5qmKpJs&color1=0xb1b1b1&color2=0xd0d0d0&hl=en_GB&feature=player_embedded&fs=1\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/iU5v5qmKpJs&color1=0xb1b1b1&color2=0xd0d0d0&hl=en_GB&feature=player_embedded&fs=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowScriptAccess=\"always\" width=\"590\" height=\"385\"></embed></object>\r\n\r\nOnly 1 day old and this owner has wrecked his new Ferrari 458.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/16/new-ferrari-458-vs-tree/','2010-08-16 04:20:55','2010-08-16 04:20:55',NULL),(1985,'Crashzone page setup for printing','crashzone-page-setup-for-printing-3','Crashzone page setup for printing','\r\n<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-header-and-footer.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone header and footer - when printing the quote\" /></p>\r\nTo remove the header and footer text when printing your Crashzone  quote\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-page-setup-in-ie.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone page setup in Internet Explorer\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>From internet Explorer</strong>\r\n\r\n* Click on file ( top left corner )\r\n* Click on page Setup\r\n* Delete all the text from the Header field\r\n* Delete all the text from the Footer field\r\n* Click OK to save the changes\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-page-setup-in-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone page setup in Firefox\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>From Firefox</strong>\r\n\r\n* Click on File ( top left corner )\r\n* Click on Page Setup\r\n* Click on Margins &amp; Header/Footer tab\r\n* Change all the drop down boxes to –blank–\r\n* Click OK to save the changes\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-printed-quote.jpg\" title=\"Crashzone printed quote example\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-printed-quote.thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone printed quote example\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For more information or help with your page setup please  contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/17/crashzone-page-setup-for-printing-3/','2010-08-17 07:22:54','2010-08-17 07:22:54',NULL),(1986,'Get Estimage on Crashzone','get-estimage-on-crashzone','Get Estimage on Crashzone','\r\n<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/mini-front-end.jpg\" alt=\"Mini front end shot\" /></p>\r\n<strong>Process for setting up Estimage on Crashzone</strong>\r\n\r\n* Contact Stelvio to download and install the Estimage program to your computer\r\n* Estimage provides you with a user name and password to access their program\r\n* Once Estimage is installed Crashzone can finalise the settings and provide training.\r\n\r\nStelvio ( Estimage )\r\nPh: 02 9761 1977\r\nWebsite: <a href=\"https://www.estimage.com/MainWeb/login.jsp\">www.estimage.com</a>\r\n\r\nInsurance companies that currently use Estimage\r\n\r\n* Lumley\r\n* Allianz\r\n* Zurich\r\n* CommInsure\r\n* Real Insurance\r\n* Bingle\r\n* Innovation\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/crashzone-estimage-user-manual-20100719.pdf\" title=\"Crashzone Estimage user manual\">Crashzone Estimage user manual</a>\r\n\r\nFor more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/18/get-estimage-on-crashzone/','2010-08-18 09:28:19','2010-08-18 09:28:19',NULL),(1987,'Crashzone how to backup your quotes','crashzone-how-to-backup-your-quotes-2','Crashzone how to backup your quotes','\r\n<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/bulletproofdoorforbank.jpg\" alt=\"Vault\" /></p>\r\nWith Crashzone you can download your backups from the setting page  anytime.\r\n\r\n* From the setting page scroll down to the backup section\r\n* Fill in the quote range for the backup\r\n* Click on ZIP to create the backup\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/crashzone-backup.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone backup settings page\" />\r\n\r\n* The backup file is sent to your email address\r\n* Open the backup email and click on the link to download your backup\r\n* Unzip the file to the location you want to store your backup\r\n\r\n* After downloading you can open up and read all your data\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/crashzone-backup-view.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone Backup view\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Backup check list</strong>\r\n<p align=\"left\">* Can you read your quote system backup disk? (<strong>Yes</strong>  with Crashzone)</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">* Does your backup include all your data? (<strong>Yes</strong>  with Crashzone)</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">* Can you read your data without your quote system  provider coming out to install/reinstall their software (<strong>Yes</strong>  with Crashzone)</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Download today your invoices, quotes, and images from   the Crashzone system. And feel safe that you do not have to rely on us   your quote system provider to read your important data.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/23/crashzone-how-to-backup-your-quotes-2/','2010-08-23 02:29:16','2010-08-23 02:29:16',NULL),(1989,'BMW Z4 sDrive35is','bmw-z4-sdrive35is','BMW Z4 sDrive35is','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/bmwz4.jpg\" alt=\"BMW Z4\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The BMW Z4 sDrive35is features a modified straight-six twin turbo engine with high precision injection technology with an output of 250 kW. Accelerating from standstill to 100 km/h in just 4.8 seconds. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.nextcar.com.au/n.bmw.z4.100820.html\">nextcar.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/25/bmw-z4-sdrive35is/','2010-08-25 04:02:56','2010-08-25 04:02:56',NULL),(1991,'10 day 100 kilometer traffic jam in China','10-day-100-kilometer-traffic-jam-in-china','10 day 100 kilometer traffic jam in China',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/china-traffic-jam.jpg\" alt=\"China traffic jam\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Triggered by road construction China,s ten day old traffic jam now stretches 100 kilometers and could last another 3 weeks. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/breaking-news/chinas-massive-traffic-jam-could-last-for-weeks/story-e6frfku0-1225909943903\">news.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/26/10-day-100-kilometer-traffic-jam-in-china/','2010-08-26 10:56:52','2010-08-26 10:56:52',NULL),(1992,'New car buyer\'s options list ','new-car-buyers-options-list','New car buyer\'s options list ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/vehicle-airbags.jpg\" alt=\"Vehicle air bags\" />\r\n\r\nNew cars have such extensive option lists it\'s hard to know which gadget is best for you.\r\n\r\n<strong>Top 10 options you should buy ... </strong>\r\n\r\n1. Electronic stability control\r\n2. Curtain airbags\r\n3. Reversing camera\r\n4. Cruise control\r\n5. Full-size spare wheel\r\n6. Parking sensors\r\n7. Keyless entry\r\n8. Bluetooth mobile hands-free kit\r\n9. iPod connectivity\r\n10. Rear-seat DVD player\r\n\r\n<strong>... and five you shouldn\'t</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Blind-spot sensors\r\n2. Soft-close doors\r\n3. Active seats\r\n4. Large-diameter, low-profile tyres on 4WDs\r\n5. Spoilers (both front and rear)\r\n\r\nFor the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/which-options-should-tick-20100826-13sqs.html\">drive.com.au </a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/30/new-car-buyers-options-list/','2010-08-30 01:34:38','2010-08-30 01:34:38',NULL),(1994,'Crashzone update ','crashzone-update-3','Crashzone update ','\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">An update has been made to the Crashzone to improve the   system and add new features. By deleting temporary files and cookies it   allows Crashzone to  do a fresh reload on your computer next time you  re  start the system. Below is a quick  guide on how to preform   the maintenance on Internet Explorer and  Firefox.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-delete-temp-files.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n\r\n( <strong>internet explorer users</strong> )\r\n* <em>from your web browser click on tools\r\n* Click on internet options\r\n* Click on delete in browsing history\r\n* Click delete files\r\n* click delete cookies</em>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cz-firefox.jpg\" alt=\"Web browser - delete temporary files and cookies\" />\r\n( <strong>Firefox users</strong> )\r\n* <em>Click on tools\r\n* Clear private data\r\n* Tick options\r\n* Click clear private data now </em>\r\n<p align=\"left\">For help please contact <a href=\"mailto:support@crashzone.com.au\"><font color=\"#666666\">support@crashzone.com.au</font></a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/01/crashzone-update-3/','2010-09-01 04:12:45','2010-09-01 04:14:16',NULL),(1996,'Insurance cost for P plates','insurance-cost-for-p-plates','Insurance cost for P plates','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/p-plate-car-crash.jpg\" title=\"P plate car accident\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/p-plate-car-crash.jpg\" alt=\"P plate car accident\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Insurance company policy is discouraging young drivers from driving  safer cars. Despite calls from road safety experts to get P-platers  behind the wheel of the latest model cars, insurance companies are  charging big money to cover new drivers. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/costs-push-pplaters-into-old-cars-20100903-14ufl.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/06/insurance-cost-for-p-plates/','2010-09-06 02:17:57','2010-09-06 02:17:57',NULL),(1998,'Automechanika Frankfurt 2010','automechanika-frankfurt-2010','Automechanika Frankfurt 2010','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/logo.jpg\" alt=\"AutoMechanica2010\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Crashzone will be visiting the Automechanika trade show next week ( 14-19 September 2010 ) in Frankfurt Germany to  report on the latest developments in the smash repairer industry. Please let us know you areas of interest and we will report on it from  the show. For more information about Automechanika 2010 please visit  their website <a href=\"http://automechanika.messefrankfurt.com/global/en/besucher/willkommen.html\">http://automechanika.messefrankfurt.com/global/en/besucher/willkommen.html</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/07/automechanika-frankfurt-2010/','2010-09-07 02:51:38','2010-09-07 02:52:31',NULL),(2000,'NACE 2010 ','nace-2010','NACE 2010 ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/nacelogo.gif\" alt=\"NACE 2010\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">October 11 -13, 2010 held at the Mandalay Bay Convention Center Las Vegas, Nevada</p>\r\nNACE, the International Autobody Congress &amp; Exposition, is the world\'s collision repair event! This year celebrates the 28th annual NACE event. Created to provide buyers and sellers within the collision repair community a place to network, NACE is the only professional event dedicated to the industry. For more information please visit the NACE website <a href=\"http://www.naceexpo.com/attendee/what-is-nace.aspx\">www.naceexpo.com</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/08/02/nace-2010/','2010-08-02 03:05:22','2010-09-07 03:08:10',NULL),(2003,'Ariel Atom 500','ariel-atom-500','Ariel Atom 500','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/arielatom1.jpg\" alt=\"Ariel 500\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/arielatom2.jpg\" alt=\"Ariel 500 - engine\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The Ariel Atom 500 powered by a 32-valve Hartley 3.0-litre V8 which was derived from  merging two Suzuki  Hayabusa 1300cc superbike four-cylinder engines together. The engine is  said to spin to 10,600rpm, like a superbike. The car that will weigh  around 500kg will easily achieve 0-160km/h in under six seconds. For the  full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/82882/ariel-atom-500-v8-built-to-celebrate-10th-birthday/\">caradvice.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/09/ariel-atom-500/','2010-09-09 03:00:37','2010-09-09 03:00:37',NULL),(2006,'Australian international motor show 2010','australian-international-motor-show-2010','Australian international motor show 2010','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/motorshow-logo.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Sydney international motor show\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/koenigsegg-ccx-rear.jpg\" alt=\"Koenigsegg CCX\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">The motor show is on again running from 15 - 24 October 2010 at Darling  Harbour Sydney. Get along to see what we will be repairing next year.  Maybe the money you saved by not paying for a quote system can be used  as a deposit for the new car you find at the show.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/10/australian-international-motor-show-2010/','2010-09-10 07:13:40','2010-09-10 07:13:40',NULL),(2007,'Crashzone - how to create a supplement quote','crashzone-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-4','Crashzone - how to create a supplement quote','\r\n<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-create-new-supplement-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement quote\" /></p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-new-supplement-button.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create a new supplement button\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\"> To create a new supplement click on the drop down box   in the quote page and select new. This will generate a blank supplement,   in this example quote 5002.1</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-items.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement items\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Add supplement/additional items to the quote. From the view page you   can view the supplement quote and the original quote. When invoicing any   supplements will be added to the original quote to give a grand total.</p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-quote-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement qutoe example\" />\r\n\r\n* Supplementary images are sent to the original quote\r\n* Use the select image function in the view page when emailing the supp quote\r\n\r\nFor further information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/13/crashzone-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-4/','2010-09-13 02:38:44','2010-09-13 02:38:44',NULL),(2008,'Crashzone works on iPhone 4','crashzone-works-on-iphone-4-2','Crashzone works on iPhone 4','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/iphone-4-using-crashzone.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone running on iPhone 4\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Use Crashzone anywhere with the iPhone4. A true mobile quoting system, for more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/15/crashzone-works-on-iphone-4-2/','2010-09-15 02:06:40','2010-09-15 02:06:40',NULL),(2010,'The Safety Show Sydney 2010','the-safety-show-sydney-2010','The Safety Show Sydney 2010','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/the-safety-show-logo.jpg\" alt=\"The Safety Show Sydeny 2010\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">This unique opportunity to find the latest OHS products all  under-one-roof, along with hundreds of new and innovative ways to  improve your workplace performance is all at The Safety Show, from the  26 to 28 October 2010 at the Sydney Showground, Sydney Olympic Park. For more information please visit <a href=\"http://www.thesafetyshow.com.au/\">www.thesafetyshow.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/16/the-safety-show-sydney-2010/','2010-09-16 03:10:09','2010-09-16 03:10:09',NULL),(2012,'FAQ - frequently asked questions - choice list using an Apple iPad','faq-frequently-asked-questions-choice-list-using-an-apple-ipad-2','FAQ - frequently asked questions - choice list using an Apple iPad','\r\n<p class=\"entry\"><img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ipad-scroll.jpg\" alt=\"Apple iPad scroll choice list\" /></p>\r\n<strong>Q:</strong> When writing a quote with an iPad how do you scroll down through the choice list ?\r\n\r\n<strong>A:</strong> Use two fingers on the screen to scroll up and down through the choice list.\r\n<p align=\"left\">Using 2 fingers over the images will also allow you to  scroll through the images. Please contact support@crashzone.com.au if  you have any questions or need help using your iPad with Crashzone.</p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/20/faq-frequently-asked-questions-choice-list-using-an-apple-ipad-2/','2010-09-20 02:13:08','2010-09-20 02:13:08',NULL),(2018,'Crashzone visiting Automechanika Frankfurt 2010 ','crashzone-visiting-automechanika-frankfurt-2010','Crashzone visiting Automechanika Frankfurt 2010 ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/automechanika11.jpg\" alt=\"Automechanika2010\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/automechanika2.jpg\" alt=\"Automechanika2010\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/automechanika3.jpg\" alt=\"Automechanika2010\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/automechanika4.jpg\" alt=\"Automechanika2010\" />\r\n\r\nStay tuned for 