ance technology has failed to avoid a crash test dummy in a media demonstration in Europe. Designed to automatically apply the brakes and avoid or  reduce injuries to pedestrians by using radar sensors and a camera, the  new Volvo V60 wagon failed to recognise the Swedish brand\'s dummy,  nicknamed Bob, in demonstrations to Australian journalists. For the full story Please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/volvo-crash-test-goes-wrong-20100925-15rak.html\">drive.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/27/volvo-demonstration-fail/','2010-09-27 04:58:13','2010-09-27 04:58:13',NULL),(2026,'Mercedes 30 years of air bag technology ','mercedes-30-years-of-air-bag-technology','Mercedes 30 years of air bag technology ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/airbag.jpg\" alt=\"Airbag\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Mercedes celebrates 30 years since introducing the first  seat belt integrated supplementary restraint system the airbag which  debuted in 1980 on the Mercedes-Benz S-Class. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/84716/mercedes-benz-celebrates-30-years-of-using-airbag-technology/\">caradvice.com.au</a><br clear=\"all\" /></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/28/mercedes-30-years-of-air-bag-technology/','2010-09-28 07:43:41','2010-09-28 07:44:44',NULL),(2027,'Crashzone works on Apple iPad','crashzone-works-on-apple-ipad-2','Crashzone works on Apple iPad','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/apple-ipad.jpg\" alt=\"Apple iPad works on Crashzone\" />',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/09/29/crashzone-works-on-apple-ipad-2/','2010-09-29 08:49:03','2010-09-29 08:49:03',NULL),(2030,'Lamborghini Sesto Elemento','lamborghini-sesto-elemento','Lamborghini Sesto Elemento','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/lamborghini1.jpg\" alt=\"Lamborghini Sesto Elemento\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/lamborghini2.jpg\" alt=\"Lamborghini Sesto Elemento\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">Weighing in at a tick under 1000kg but fitted with a mighty 419kW V10  engine that sends its power to all four wheels, the brand\'s newest  addition is said to be able to reach 100km/h in just 2.5 seconds. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/lamborghinis-onetonne-wonder-20100930-15xuh.html\">drive.com.au</a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/10/01/lamborghini-sesto-elemento/','2010-10-01 08:51:53','2010-10-01 08:51:53',NULL),(2034,'Jaguar C-X75 Concept ','jaguar-c-x75-concept','Jaguar C-X75 Concept ',' <img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/jaguar-cx75.jpg\" alt=\"Jaguar CX75\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/jaguar-cx75-1.jpg\" alt=\"Jaguar CX75\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/jaguar-cx75-2.jpg\" alt=\"Jaguar CX75\" />\r\n<p align=\"left\">At each wheel of the Jaguar C-X75 there\'s a 145kW electric motor, which  combine to deliver 580kW and help propel the 1350kg supercar to 100km/h  in just 3.4 seconds on the way to a top speed of 330km/h. The car uses 2  helicopter like turbines to charge the batteries which feed the 4  electric motors. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/jaguars-helicopterinspired-supercar-20100930-15xvx.html\">drive.com.au </a></p>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/2010/10/05/jaguar-c-x75-concept/','2010-10-05 02:29:05','2010-10-05 02:29:05',NULL),(2037,'Ford Falcon GT supercharged ','ford-falcon-gt-supercharged','Ford Falcon GT supercharged ','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/falcon-gt.jpg\" alt=\"Ford Falcon GT\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/falcon-gt