3/cz-printed-quote-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor more information or help with your page setup please contact support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=2524','2011-03-02 02:29:44','2011-03-02 02:29:44',NULL),(2530,'','2530','','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ipad21.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2532\" title=\"Apple ipad2\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ipad21.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"236\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe new Apple iPad 2 has been released today, it is more powerful and thinner than the previous model and best of all it now has a built in Camera. This means you will be able add photos while writing the quote on your iPad 2. The Australian release date will be around the 25th of March 2011. For more information please visit <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/au/ipad/\">http://www.apple.com/au/ipad/</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=2530','2011-03-03 00:35:42','2011-03-03 00:35:42',NULL),(2537,'Collision Repair Expo','collision-repair-expo-3','Collision Repair Expo','<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Collision-Repair-Expo-2011.jpg\"><img title=\"Collision Repair Expo 2011\" src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Collision-Repair-Expo-2011.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"101\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Come along and visit Crashzone at the Collision Repair Expo stand AB45</strong>\r\n\r\nHosted by the Australian Automotive Aftermarket Association (AAAA),   the COLLISION REPAIR EXPO will be held from Thursday 12 – Saturday 14   May 2011 at the Melbourne Exhibition Centre, in conjunction with the   Australian Auto Aftermarket Expo. please visit <a href=\"http://www.collisionrepair.com.au/\">www.collisionrepair.com.au</a>\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=2537','2011-03-07 00:34:51','2011-03-07 00:34:51',NULL),(2541,'Digital camera image size','digital-camera-image-size-5','Digital camera image size','<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2009/07/cz-image-size.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone image size setting on digital camera\" />\r\n\r\nWith most digital point-and-shoot cameras, you can actually choose a  lower resolution than the camera’s advertised maximum, which is where  it’s set when you take it out of the box. You do this by entering the  shooting menu and selecting the “Image Size” or “Resolution” option.  When you do that, you’ll see a series of number pairs such as these:\r\n\r\n* 3648 x 2736 or 10 megapixel ( 1.1 MB to 2.2 MB approx)\r\n* 3264 x 2448 or 8 megapixel ( 970 KB to 1.9 MB approx )\r\n* 2048 x 1536  or 3.1 megapixel ( 500 KB to 1 MB approx )\r\n* 1600 x 1200 or 1.9 megapixel ( 250 KB to 700KB approx )\r\n* 1280 x 960 or 1.2 megapixel ( 240 KB to 490 KB approx )\r\n* 1024 x 768 or 0.8 megapixel ( 170 KB to 350 KB approx )\r\n<strong>* 640 x 480 or VGA ( 75 KB to 150 KB approx )   – ORM, PNET, ARNIE setting\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nSetting a lower resolution level creates a smaller-sized picture  file. When you adjust the resolution downward, you’ll see the little  number on the viewing screen and/or LCD panel that tells you how many  more pictures you can fit on the card go up and up. Set 640 x 480, and  you’ll be able to fit hundreds if not thousands of pictures on a  decent-sized memory card.\r\n\r\nWhen emailing images a lower/lowest setting on your camera is always  best this will allow you send  images quickly and make it easier for  your customer to download and store the images you send to them.\r\n\r\nFor more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=2541','2013-04-29 01:03:07','2013-04-29 01:36:35',NULL),(2545,'Crashzone Jobsheet','crashzone-jobsheet','Crashzone Jobsheet','<div>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2008/12/crashzone-header-page1.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone header page - Work sheet\" />\r\n\r\nFrom the settings page select your preferred style of jobsheet.\r\n* <strong>Picture</strong> - shows a large photo of the vehicle with all the owners details.\r\n* <strong>Detail </strong>- shows the owners details + the labour description and operation times.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2008/12/crashzone-header-settings.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone header settings\" />\r\n\r\nFrom the view page click on the sub tab \"Header\" the jobsheet will be displayed on the page.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/CZ-job-sheet.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2547\" title=\"CZ job sheet\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/CZ-job-sheet.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"268\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=2545','2016-02-01 00:00:55','2016-03-04 04:05:15',NULL),(2557,'Important notice – refresh you web browser','important-notice-%e2%80%93-refresh-you-web-browser','Important notice – refresh you web browser','<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Refresh-web-browser.jpg\"><img title=\"Refresh web browser\" src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Refresh-web-browser.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"589\" height=\"202\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Important notice:</strong>\r\nAn update has been made to the Crashzone system 11/03/2011\r\n\r\nTo make sure your computer is running the latest version of Crashzone  please refresh your web browser 3 times next time you login to  Crashzone.\r\nTo refresh click on the <strong>refresh symbol</strong> in your web browser or use the <strong>F5</strong> key on your keyboard. Any questions please contact  support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=2557','2011-03-14 00:14:44','2011-03-14 00:14:44',NULL),(2563,'KW PANELS - features in the MITA newsletter','kw-panels-features-in-the-mit