e-how-to-backup-your-quotes-4','Crashzone how to backup your quotes','<div>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2009/08/bulletproofdoorforbank.jpg\" alt=\"Vault\" />\r\n\r\nWith Crashzone you can download your backups from the setting page  anytime.\r\n\r\n* From the setting page scroll down to the backup section\r\n* Fill in the quote range for the backup\r\n* Click on ZIP to create the backup\r\n\r\n<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2009/08/crashzone-backup.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone backup settings page\" />\r\n\r\n* The backup file is sent to your email address\r\n* Open the backup email and click on the link to download your backup\r\n* Unzip the file to the location you want to store your backup\r\n\r\n* After downloading you can open up and read all your data\r\n\r\n<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2009/08/crashzone-backup-view.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone Backup view\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Backup check list</strong>\r\n\r\n* Can you read your quote system backup disk? (<strong>Yes</strong> with Crashzone)\r\n\r\n* Does your backup include all your data? (<strong>Yes</strong> with Crashzone)\r\n\r\n* Can you read your data without your quote system  provider coming out to install/reinstall their software (<strong>Yes</strong> with Crashzone)\r\n\r\nDownload today your invoices, quotes, and images from   the Crashzone system. And feel safe that you do not have to rely on us   your quote system provider to read your important data.\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=3711','2012-07-13 01:35:22','2012-07-13 01:35:22',NULL),(3716,'How to add a 2nd colour in the paint section','how-to-add-a-2nd-colour-in-the-paint-section-2','How to add a 2nd colour in the paint section','<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2010/01/crashzone-2nd-colour-on-quote.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone 2nd colour on quote\" />\r\n\r\n* From the choice list select miscellaneous and then click on “2nd colour”\r\n* This will add a new line to the quote “2nd colour”\r\n* Add your 2nd colour items to the quote\r\n* Fill in the 2nd colour rate in the rate box\r\n* Add the labour time for the  item\r\n\r\n<img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2010/01/crashzone-2nd-colour-rate.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone 2nd colour rate shown on quote\" />\r\n\r\n* On the viewed quote the rate for the 2nd colour is shown in the description.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or need help with adding a 2nd colour please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=3716','2011-11-09 01:18:03','2011-11-09 01:18:03',NULL),(3722,'Crashzone update - 11/11/2011','crashzone-update-11112011','Crashzone update - 11/11/2011','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/lamborghini.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3724\" title=\"lamborghini\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/lamborghini.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"263\" /></a>\r\n\r\nCrashzone will make an update to the system tonight 11/11/2011 at approx 7pm Sydney time.\r\nIncluded in this update:\r\n\r\nNTAR - vehicle and times updated.\r\nIE9 - Internet Explorer 9 compatibility fixed.\r\nComments section - comments from details page can shown on quote.\r\nPNET issue - sending supp quotes.\r\nPNET issue - receiving multiple request for quotes for the same vehicle.\r\nPNET issue - receiving manual quotes.\r\n\r\nAny problems or questions please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=3722','2011-11-11 02:14:56','2011-11-11 02:21:13',NULL),(3734,'Important notice ','important-notice-6','Important notice ','Due to a system error on one of our servers it was necessary to do a reboot at approx 5pm ( Sydney time ) This caused some system outage but the system is up and running as normal now. Any customer experiencing problems should contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=3734','2011-11-16 10:03:18','2011-11-16 10:03:18',NULL),(3741