crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/MTA-Crisis-meeting-31.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4407\" title=\"MTA Crisis meeting \" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/MTA-Crisis-meeting-31.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"178\" /></a>\r\n\r\nBig turn out from the smash repair industry.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/MTA-Crisis-meeting-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4408\" title=\"MTA Crisis meeting 1\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/MTA-Crisis-meeting-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"397\" /></a>\r\n\r\nA good mix of guest speakers for the night, including MTA, Repairers and suppliers.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/MTA-Crisis-meeting-2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4409\" title=\"MTA Crisis meeting 2\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/MTA-Crisis-meeting-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"309\" /></a>\r\n\r\nRuss &amp; Lisa down from QLD for the meeting.\r\nCheck out the Crashzone forum for feedback from Russ.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4404','2012-06-04 03:39:53','2012-06-04 03:41:40',NULL);
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (4415,'Hyundai Smash Hits Program','hyundai-smash-hits-program','Hyundai Smash Hits Program','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/HyundaiSmashHitsCover.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4416\" title=\"Hyundai Smash Hits\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/HyundaiSmashHitsCover.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"416\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Hyundai smashes their prices on accident repair parts </strong>\r\n\r\nIf you’re wondering why you’re seeing so many Hyundai vehicles on the road today, there’s a perfectly good reason for it. Over the past four years, Hyundai has recorded continuous sales growth, making Hyundai Automotive Group the world’s fifth largest major automotive manufacturer and the fastest growing automotive brand in the world. Hyundai has worked tirelessly to produce quality cars that exceed the expectations of their customers. That is why Hyundai has earned unprecedented acclaim and recognition from independent motoring journalists and automotive governing bodies around the world.\r\n\r\nHyundai prides itself on three key ingredients; affordability, reliability, and excellent quality. Owning a vehicle can be very expensive, especially if you are in an accident and need to purchase repair parts. Hyundai Genuine Parts are widely perceived as being more expensive than the non-genuine equivalent, but this is not always the case. Not only are Hyundai Genuine Parts competitively priced but they are engineered to integrate with a particular Hyundai vehicle ensuring the vehicle is not compromised. They also undergo rigorous testing to ensure that they meet all of the Australian standards, which is unlikely to be undertaken by the manufacturers of non-genuine products.\r\n\r\nThe automotive parts market is full of cheap and inferior substitutes. Non-genuine parts are sold at considerably reduced prices because their manufacturer does not bear any research, development or advertising costs. Although non-genuine parts look almost identical to Hyundai Genuine Parts, there is however much discrepancy between them. Where the research or testing has not been undertaken, those non- genuine parts may have a high likelihood of being a serious safety threat. Further, those products would be likely to have a poor fit, have an undetermined crash resistance and unknown mechanical reliability.\r\n\r\nTo compete with this market, Hyundai Motor Company Australia has re-launched their Smash Hits program for 2012 which offers up to 20% off the list price of Hyundai Genuine Parts. There are over 200 discounted Accident Repair Parts for Getz, Elantra, i30, Tuscon, Santa Fe; and iload and iMax models. Not only is Hyundai Motor Company Australia realigning its prices, they are also rewarding Smash Repairers with some fabulous prizes.\r\n\r\nRegistered Smash Repairers who purchase Smash Hits parts within the promotional period (3rd October 2011- 28th September 2012) can win prizes such as Nespresso Coffee Machines, Snap On Tools Vouchers, iPod Sound Systems, Full HD 3D LCD TVs or a Hyundai i20 courtesy car. For every dollar they spend on parts, they will receive one entry into the draw. The more parts they purchase, the greater their chances are of winning a prize! Visit <a href=\"http://www.hyundaismashhits.com.au\">www.hyundaismashhits.com.au</a> for more information.\r\n\r\nThere is no substitute for Hyundai Genuine Parts. For quality, guaranteed fit and safety, insist on Hyundai Genuine Parts. Contact your Hyundai Dealership to register for the Smash Hits program and keep your customers vehicles the way they want them - safe, reliable and guaranteed.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4415','2012-11-04 23:07:56','2012-11-05 00:25:20',NULL),(4427,'Crashzone iPhone App update ','crashzone-iphone-app-update','Crashzone iPhone App update ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/iPhone-update.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4428\" title=\"iPhone update\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/iPhone-update.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"305\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe latest update for the Crashzone iPhone App is now available from the App Store.\r\nThe Crashzone App will now save a copy of the photos to your phone album when you take them. For more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4427','2012-06-08 04:41:30','2012-06-08 04:41:30',NULL),(4433,'Fourteen Ferrari drivers booked for speeding ','fourteen-ferrari-drivers-booked-for-speeding','Fourteen Ferrari drivers booked for speeding ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Ferrari.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4434\" title=\"Ferrari\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Ferrari.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"328\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne <strong>Ferrari</strong> owner in China has had his car impounded  and four more have had their licences suspended after police in Zhejiang  Province clocked a convoy of 14 Prancing Horse drivers speeding on  Saturday. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/176560/fourteen-ferrari-drivers-clocked-speeding-in-china/\">caradvice.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4433','2012-06-13 08:40:51','2012-06-13 08:40:51',NULL),(4438,'Illegal pit crews steal tyres ','illegal-pit-crews-steal-tyres','Illegal pit crews steal tyres ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/stolenwheels.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4440\" title=\"stolen wheels\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/stolenwheels.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"589\" height=\"262\" /></a>\r\n\r\nA Honda dealership in the NewYork was recently the target of an audacious   heist of 72 wheels that left rows of gleaming new cars perched on cinder   blocks. For the full story please visit<a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/illegal-pit-crews-steal-tyres-20120608-2000l.html\"> news.com.au</a>\r\n\r\nhttp://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/illegal-pit-crews-steal-tyres-20120608-2000l.html',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4438','2012-06-15 02:33:19','2012-06-15 02:33:19',NULL),(4444,'John\'s Twins Accident Repair Centre - Wollongong repairer','johns-twins-accident-repair-centre-wollongong-repairer','John\'s Twins Accident Repair Centre - Wollongong repairer','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Johns_Twins-smash.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4462\" title=\"JohnsTwins Smash\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Johns_Twins-smash.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"327\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>John\'s Twins Accident Repair Centre</strong>\r\n\r\n346 Keira Street, Wollongong 2500\r\n<strong>Phone</strong>: (02) 4226 6044\r\n<strong>Email</strong>: <a href=\"info@johnstwins.com.au\">info@johnstwins.com.au</a>\r\n<strong>Website:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.johnstwins.com.au/ \">www.johnstwins.com.au\r\n</a> <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Johns_Twins-smash-map.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4463\" title=\"Johns_Twins Smash map\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Johns_Twins-smash-map.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"350\" height=\"240\" /></a>',0,0,1,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4444','2012-06-19 03:21:40','2012-06-19 03:21:40',NULL),(4469,'Crashzone - how to setup Estimage','crashzone-how-to-setup-estimage','Crashzone - how to setup Estimage','<div>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/mini-front-end.jpg\" alt=\"Mini front end shot\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Process for setting up Estimage on Crashzone</strong>\r\n\r\n* Contact Stelvio to download and install the Estimage program to your computer\r\n* Please note Stelvio charge you a yearly support fee\r\n* Estimage provides you with a user name and password to access their program\r\n* Once Estimage is installed Crashzone can finalise the settings and provide training.\r\n\r\nStelvio ( Estimage )\r\n\r\nPhone Number: 02 9455 1000\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 300;\">Estimage Support: 02 9455 1055</p>\r\nWebsite: <a href=\"https://www.estimage.com/MainWeb/login.jsp\">www.estimage.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Crashzone Estimage user manual\" href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/crashzone-estimage-user-manual-20100719.pdf\">Crashzone Estimage user manual</a>\r\n\r\nFor more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4469','2017-09-25 02:00:39','2017-10-31 22:54:40',NULL),(4476,'Classic Holden found with 998km on the clock','classic-holden-found-with-998km-on-the-clock','Classic Holden found with 998km on the clock','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Kingswood.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4477\" title=\"Kingswood\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Kingswood.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"309\" /></a>\r\n\r\nA 1979 Holden Kingswood in pristine condition with just 998km on the odometer has been unearthed as part of a deceased estate. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/not-the-kingswood-20120626-20zm3.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4476','2012-06-26 08:54:32','2012-06-26 08:54:32',NULL),(4480,'Crashzone iPhone application','crashzone-iphone-application','Crashzone iPhone application','<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/iPhoneCZ1.jpg\"><img title=\"Crashzone iPhone App\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/iPhoneCZ1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"380\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe application allow you to take photos with you iPhone and instantly upload them to your Crashzone quote.\r\n\r\n* Download the application from the App store\r\n* Compatible with iPhone 4 or 4s\r\n* To setup enter you company ID number in the setting\r\n* Take photos with the App\r\n\r\nPlease contact support@crashzone.com.au to get your company ID when doing the setup.\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4480','2012-10-11 23:00:41','2012-10-11 23:29:02',NULL),(4485,'Thieves target Holden engines','thieves-target-holden-engines','Thieves target Holden engines','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/holden.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4487\" title=\"Holden\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/holden.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"301\" /></a>\r\n\r\nPolice believe motors and transmissions stolen from the company\'s  Elizabeth site, north of Adelaide, have been sold through car clubs  locally and along the east coast and on internet sites such as eBay. For the full story please visit<a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/business/companies/thieves-target-holden-engines-in-25-million-theft/story-fnda1bsz-1226413416774\"> news.com.au</a>\r\n<div></div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4485','2012-07-02 04:31:14','2012-07-02 04:31:14',NULL),(4492,'Holden Volt in Australia','holden-volt-in-australia','Holden Volt in Australia','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/holden-volt.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4494\" title=\"holden-volt\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/holden-volt.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"296\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHolden has confirmed the $59,990 price for the volt which will be available in Australia later this year.\r\nThe Volt is propelled by a 16.5-kWh lithium-ion battery and electric  motor that has an estimated 111kW and 370Nm and can provide a pure  electric range of up to 87km.\r\nThe vehicle also has a 1.4-litre  petrol engine that is used purely to keep a charge in the battery - not  drive the wheels directly - to give a range of more than 600km depending  on driving conditions. for the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/national/holden-launches-affordable-volt-electric-vehicle/story-fncynjr2-1226414953564\">news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4492','2012-07-04 05:46:11','2012-07-04 05:46:11',NULL),(4501,'Ken Block - GYMKHANA FIVE','ken-block-gymkhana-five','Ken Block - GYMKHANA FIVE','<iframe width=\"590\" height=\"332\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/LuDN2bCIyus\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\nThis is the latest video from Ken Block well worth a look.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4501','2012-07-16 01:29:34','2012-07-16 01:29:34',NULL),(4504,'Get Crashzone with PNET, ORM, ARNIE & Estimage','get-crashzone-with-pnet-orm-arnie-estimage-3','Get Crashzone with PNET, ORM, ARNIE & Estimage','<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Lamborghini.jpg\"><img title=\"Crashzone \" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Lamborghini.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you pay a yearly support fee for your quoting software ?</strong>\r\n\r\nGet  Crashzone today, we don’t charge any support fee and  definitely    don’t charge for upgrades made to PNET, ORM, ARNIE or  Estimage.\r\n\r\nCreate your own Crashzone system today no obligation no  hidden    catches guaranteed. For more information please contact     support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4504','2012-07-18 03:38:47','2012-07-18 03:38:47',NULL),(4511,'Chrome Lexus LFA','chrome-lexus-lfa','Chrome Lexus LFA','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Chrome-Lexus1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4513\" title=\"Chrome-Lexus\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Chrome-Lexus1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"312\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAn owner of one of just 10 Lexus supercars coming to Australia – and  only 500 in the world – has had his $700,000 car covered in chrome. For the full story please visit\r\n<a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/the-700000-chrome-car-20120719-22c8p.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4511','2012-07-24 03:46:26','2012-07-24 03:46:26',NULL),(4516,'Crashzone – how to create a supplement quote','crashzone-%e2%80%93-how-to-create-a-supplement-quote-3','Crashzone – how to create a supplement quote','<div>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/cz-new-supp1.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone create new supp quote\" />\r\n\r\nTo create a new supplement quote click on the drop down box    in the quote page and select <strong>New Supp</strong>. This will generate a blank  supplement,   in this example quote 5002.1\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-items.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement items\" />\r\n\r\nAdd supplement/additional items to the quote. From the    view page you   can view the supplement quote and the original quote.    When invoicing any   supplements will be added to the original quote to    give a grand total.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/crashzone-supplement-quote-example.jpg\" alt=\"Crashzone supplement qutoe example\" />\r\n\r\n* Supplementary images are sent to the original quote\r\n* Use the select image function in the view page when emailing the supp quote\r\n\r\nFor further information please contact support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4516','2012-07-25 02:47:42','2012-07-25 02:47:42',NULL),(4519,'Simple quoting with Apple iPad','simple-quoting-with-apple-ipad','Simple quoting with Apple iPad','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/cz-using-ipad1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4520\" title=\"iPad with Crashzone\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/cz-using-ipad1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"387\" /></a>\r\n\r\nMobile quoting anywhere using Crashzone with an Apple iPad. For more information please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4519','2012-12-16 23:00:25','2012-12-17 01:06:37',NULL),(4530,'Light cars worse of in accidents','light-cars-worse-of-in-accidents','Light cars worse of in accidents','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Car-accident.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4532\" title=\"Car accident\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Car-accident.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"256\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhile most new light cars score four or a maximum five stars in the  Australian New Car Assessment Program (ANCAP), they are disadvantaged by  their weight when crashing into bigger and heavier vehicle. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/national/light-city-cars-high-ancap-ratings-do-not-protect-in-real-world-crashes/story-fncynjr2-1226446197372\">news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4530','2012-08-10 01:11:54','2012-08-10 01:11:54',NULL),(4537,'Crashzone - parts management','crashzone-parts-management','Crashzone - parts management','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/parts-management.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4538\" title=\"Crashzone parts management\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/parts-management.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"580\" height=\"312\" /></a>\r\n\r\nCrashzone has a new feature for parts management. With the new feature enabled you can track your parts within Crashzone. Enter list price, cost price, mark parts as quoted, ordered, received &amp; credited. Send a price request as a link for your dealer to fill in and automatically update in Crashzone. For more information please <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/helpfile/Crashzone-Parts-Ordering-User-Manual.pdf\">download the parts user manual</a> or contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4537','2012-08-14 03:59:32','2012-08-14 03:59:32',NULL),(4546,'Something to watch out for ','something-to-watch-out-for','Something to watch out for ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Greatwallmotors.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4547\" title=\"Greatwallmotors\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Greatwallmotors.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"295\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlmost 24,000 budget-priced Chinese cars have been recalled over  <strong>asbestos fears</strong>, but instead of being fixed immediately, they will have  warning stickers attached. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/asbestos-parts-in-recalled-cars-wont-be-replaced-20120815-247jv.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4546','2012-08-16 06:54:40','2012-08-16 06:54:40',NULL),(4552,'Crashzone add images to the quote drag & drop','crashzone-add-images-to-the-quote-drag-drop-4','Crashzone add images to the quote drag & drop','<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/dragdrop.jpg\"><img title=\"Crashzone drag &amp; drop images\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/dragdrop.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"366\" /></a>\r\nUsing <a href=\"http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/\">Firefox</a> customers can now add images simply by dragging them onto the details page in Crashzone.\r\n\r\n* Have you quote open in the details page of Crashzone\r\n* Open your Picture folder ( where you save you images )\r\n* Highlight the image you want to add to the quote\r\n* Left click on the images and hold down the mouse and drag the images to the details page on Crashzone.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/dragdrop1.jpg\"><img title=\"Drag &amp; Drop images Crashzone\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/dragdrop1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"201\" /></a>\r\n\r\n* The images will upload to the quote, a green loading bar appears below the images while the upload is in progress.\r\n\r\n<strong>Please note</strong>:\r\n<em>Maximum image size is 2mb per image\r\nYou can drag up to 10 images at once\r\nThis feature currently only works with Firefox web browser.</em>\r\n\r\nFor questions or help using the drag and drop feature please contact support@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4552','2012-08-20 05:39:26','2012-08-20 05:39:26',NULL),(4556,'Ford GT40 fetches US$11 million','ford-gt40-fetches-us11-million','Ford GT40 fetches US$11 million','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/GT40.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4557\" title=\"Ford GT40\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/GT40.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"237\" /></a>\r\n\r\nA race-bred Ford GT40 has set a new record for the highest price paid for an American car sold at auction fetching US $ 11 million dollars. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://news.drive.com.au/drive/motor-news/le-mans-ford-gt40-fetches-us11-million-20120821-24jh3.html\">drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=4556','2012-08-22 07:11:59','2012-08-22 07:11:59',NULL),(4562,'How to update hourly rates in Crashzone','how-to-update-hourly-rates-in-crashzone-2','How t