,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6284','2014-08-25 03:36:02','2014-08-25 03:36:02',NULL),(6288,'Grand Cherokee recalled over turn signal problem','grand-cherokee-recalled-over-turn-signal-problem','Grand Cherokee recalled over turn signal problem','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rsz_jeep.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6290\" title=\"Jeep\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rsz_jeep.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"473\" height=\"224\" /></a>\r\nAs such, vehicles impacted by the fault “may pose an accident hazard to the driver and other road users”, as their indicators may not work and the driver may not be aware the blinkers are failing. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/304282/2014-jeep-grand-cherokee-recalled-over-turn-signal-problem/\">caradvice.com.au</a> - I did not think Jeep drivers used their indicators :)',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6288','2014-09-01 01:42:57','2014-09-01 01:42:57',NULL),(6294,'Need a new car ? You may soon be able to directly import one','need-a-new-car-you-may-soon-be-able-to-directly-import-one','Need a new car ? You may soon be able to directly import one','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rsz_porsche-911-gt3-orange.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6295\" title=\"porsche-911-gt3\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rsz_porsche-911-gt3-orange.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"507\" height=\"189\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAUSTRALIANS may soon be able to buy a new car directly from overseas. As the demise of the local car manufacturing industry approaches, the Federal Government is considering a change. It has included the idea among options in a discussion paper being released Thursday. “The discussion paper will consider personal importation of new vehicles to provide consumers with greater choice to … purchase a new (vehicle) from overseas, provided it satisfies Australia’s safety standards. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/national/need-a-new-car-you-may-soon-be-able-to-directly-import-one/story-fncynjr2-1227046876550\">news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6294','2014-09-04 04:26:47','2014-09-04 04:26:47',NULL),(6305,'$16 million fleet of bombproof limousines for G20','16-million-fleet-of-bombproof-limousines-for-g20','$16 million fleet of bombproof limousines for G20','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/S-guard.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6306\" title=\"S guard\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/S-guard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"287\" /></a>\r\n\r\nBut rather than buy the vehicles for $1 million each, it has rented them for the meeting of world leaders at a cost of $1.8 million, or $112,500 a piece. The bombproof Benzes can withstand firepower from an AK47 assault rifle, are fitted with nail-proof tyres, and have their own on-board oxygen systems in case of a chemical weapon attack. For the full story please visit news.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6305','2014-09-09 01:33:25','2014-09-09 01:33:25',NULL),(6311,'Happy Friday Crashzone','happy-friday-crashzone','Happy Friday Crashzone','<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/BUREX8aFbMs?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\nNothing to do with the automotive industry but well worth watching :)',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6311','2014-09-12 01:19:47','2014-09-12 01:19:47',NULL),(6319,'Digital imaging for quoting accident repairs','digital-imaging-for-quoting-accident-repairs-2','Digital imaging for quoting accident repairs','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/images.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6320\" title=\"images\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/images.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"75\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWith the ever increasing demand by insurers for assessments by digital imaging, here are a few tips from an experienced assessor on this subject.\r\n\r\n<strong>The No 1 Cardinal Rule is “If you could not quote from the photos how do you expect the assessor to assess the damage from these photos.”\r\n</strong>\r\nGood quotes and good photos get proper and fair assessments.\r\nIt saves your valuable time just to take a little more time initially taking proper and sufficient numbers of photographs than having to be requested by the assessor to send more because they can not clearly see all the damage you have quoted. Digital photography is quick and easy, just click &amp; save.\r\n\r\n<strong>Camera Settings:</strong>\r\n\r\nSome very high quality digital cameras are on the market today some boasting 16 megapixels or more.For digital images for transmission over the internet, high resolution settings are <strong>DEFINITELY NOT THE WAY TO GO</strong>.\r\nHigh resolution is fine if you want to print high quality photos; however these take a large slice of computer memory and take a long time to send.  In some cases services will not accept large files and your emails will be rejected. There is little or no difference in the detail of the image seen on the computer screen between high and low resolution. For the purposes of images with quotes, settings of less than 1 megapixel are quite adequate.  (the setting we use is 640×480)  These will transmit quickly and take up much less memory on your computers hard drive.\r\nThe resolution setting on all digital cameras are easily adjustable.\r\n\r\n<strong>Photos of the Damage</strong>\r\n\r\nApproach the photography in the same way you look at the vehicle and the damage when you write you quote.\r\n\r\nYour photos should include:-\r\n\r\n1. An overview of the whole vehicle. (the rego no if registered).\r\n2. The vehicle badges to identify the model.\r\n3. Compliance Plate, Paint Code (very important).\r\n4. Engine &amp; Transmission type.\r\n5. Registration Label and Odometer Reading.\r\n\r\nYou are now ready for the damage in detail.\r\n\r\n1. Overview of the damaged area.  Stand back just a little as you would when you first look at the damage.\r\n2. Then take a closer photo which shows the damage in more detail. (Remember to let the camera focus before you click the shutter).  In some cases you may need to adjust the camera settings to MACRO for really close shots.\r\n3. Take photos from different angles just as though you would move your angle of sight looking at the damage.\r\n4. Where possible remove parts such as bar covers so the damage behind can be exposed.\r\n5. Avoid using the flash as much as possible especially for close ups. (the image whites out with the flash)\r\n\r\nIt is suggested you photograph all the vehicles you quote, firstly for your own records, (helps if the owner tries to tell you “this damage was not there when we left the vehicle with you”) and secondly it will save more time if you don’t have to request the owner or third party to call back for photos.\r\n\r\nAnd Remember:\r\n\r\n<strong>The No 1 Cardinal Rule is “If you could not quote from the photos how do you expect the assessor to assess the damage from these photos.”</strong>\r\n\r\nFollow these easy steps and you will save much of your valuable time and get the work authority much sooner.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6319','2014-09-18 01:59:31','2014-09-18 01:59:51',NULL),(6336,'The Crashzone Community Repairer Network has been launched this week','the-crashzone-community-repairer-network-has-been-launched-this-week','The Crashzone Community Repairer Network has been launched this week','<strong>PRESS RELEASE:</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CCRN.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6384\" title=\"CCRN\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CCRN.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"155\" />\r\n</a>\r\nThe Crashzone Community Repairer Network has been launched this week.\r\n\r\nThe feeling among all the shops involved is that this friendly collaboration is enhancing the knowledge base of all Crashzone repairers. This information sharing is also creating opportunities for work providers to deal with the largest Australia wide network of repairers.\r\nThe Crashzone Community Repairer Network potential is unrivalled in population coverage.\r\nOne of the network goals is to reinforce the public perception that the Repairers are the experts.\r\nThe Insurers will welcome the support that the Crashzone network will bring.\r\nClick on the link below for a copy of the Crashzone Community Repairer Network code of conduct\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Crashzone-Membership-Code-of-Conduct-2014-amended-draft-2.pdf\">Code of Conduct </a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6336','2014-10-10 01:20:05','2014-10-10 02:32:15',NULL),(6339,'Lamborghini poo prank','lamborghini-poo-prank','Lamborghini poo prank','<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/eD6Qq1iROMA?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6339','2014-10-02 02:02:35','2014-10-02 02:02:35',NULL),(6342,'Chinese utes slammed again','chinese-utes-slammed-again','Chinese utes slammed again','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/crashtest.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6347\" title=\"crashtest\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/crashtest.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"280\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe reputation of Chinese utes has taken another hit as the latest crash tests award just three stars out of five for safety — and sales continue to free fall after the asbestos scare of 2012. For the full story please visit<a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/finance/business/chinese-utes-slammed-again-for-poor-crash-safety-rating-as-australian-sales-slide/story-fnda1bsz-1227067078593\"> www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6342','2014-10-01 00:12:20','2014-10-01 00:12:20',NULL),(6354,'Ford police car 800hp','ford-police-car-800hp','Ford police car 800hp','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/police-car.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6418\" title=\"Ford GT Police car\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/police-car.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"288\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe NSW highway patrol have taken delivery of one of the last ever Ford Falcon GT sedans — which, in a one-off special, has a supercharged V8 engine tuned by racing legend Dick Johnson to a staggering 800 horsepower. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/design/dick-johnson-tunes-a-ford-falcon-gtf-australias-most-powerful-police-car/story-fnjwucvh-1227076729084\">www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6354','2014-10-12 01:05:56','2014-11-07 01:41:10',NULL),(6363,'Crashzone community survey ','crashzone-community-survey','Crashzone community survey ','<strong>Update:\r\n07/10/2014\r\nCrashzone community survey</strong>\r\n\r\nThank you to everyone that has participated in the survey, we have had a good response and a lot of feedback. If you did not participate you can still click on the link below. I will publish some general statistics later this week :)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://crashzone.wufoo.com/forms/crashzoneas-community-repairer-network/\">https://crashzone.wufoo.com/forms/crashzoneas-community-repairer-network/</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>02/10/2014\r\nCrashzone community survey - 2 minutes of your time please </strong>\r\n\r\nCrashzone users,\r\nWe sent out a mass email to with the survey below\r\n* To anyone that got multiple emails my apologies, mass emails can be tricky.\r\n* To anyone that could not open the link you can try clicking on the link below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://crashzone.wufoo.com/forms/crashzoneas-community-repairer-network/\">https://crashzone.wufoo.com/forms/crashzoneas-community-repairer-network/</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6363','2014-10-02 07:50:17','2014-10-07 04:35:21',NULL),(6367,'Queensland Repair Forum - meeting 09/10/2014','queensland-repair-forum-meeting-09102014','Queensland Repair Forum - meeting 09/10/2014','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/QRF.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6368\" title=\"QRF\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/QRF.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"772\" /></a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6367','2014-10-08 02:48:21','2014-10-10 04:11:22',NULL),(6400,'“huge photo of breasts’’ causes hundreds of car accidents','%e2%80%9chuge-photo-of-breasts%e2%80%99%e2%80%99-causes-hundreds-of-car-accidents','“huge photo of breasts’’ causes hundreds of car accidents','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/advert.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6401\" title=\"advert\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/advert.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"280\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe ad campaign is certainly designed to get your attention but it backfired in a big way when it caused over 500 road accidents in a single day. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/world/truck-with-huge-photo-of-breasts-causes-hundreds-of-car-accidents/story-fndir2ev-1227093022050\">news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6400','2014-10-11 23:53:42','2014-10-16 23:57:41',NULL),(6405,'Motorists to pay more for car servicing','motorists-to-pay-more-for-car-servicing','Motorists to pay more for car servicing','<div id=\"_mcePaste\"><a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/car.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6406\" title=\"car\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/car.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"263\" /></a></div>\r\nLOCAL mechanics could soon become extinct and motorists may be forced to pay more for vehicle servicing after the car industry blocked independent repairers from getting access to complete maintenance data and specialist tools to fix modern cars. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/finance/business/motorists-to-pay-more-for-car-servicing-under-new-regulations/story-fnkgdhrc-1227095455020\">www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6405','2014-10-12 01:00:42','2014-10-21 00:23:30',NULL),(6413,'Hot lap in Audi\'s self-driving RS7','hot-lap-in-audis-self-driving-rs7','Hot lap in Audi\'s self-driving RS7','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/AudiRS7.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6414\" title=\"AudiRS7\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/AudiRS7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"274\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAnother day of testing at the track, one might casually surmise. However, this is far from your ordinary new car evaluation.\r\nWhy? Because no one is behind the steering wheel of the five-door liftback as it arcs into the tight left-hander right at the limit of adhesion before switching direction into a long, tightening radius right hand corner. For the full story please visit<a href=\"http://www.drive.com.au/motor-news/hot-lap-in-audis-selfdriving-rs7-20141020-118jic.html\"> www.drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6413','2014-10-12 01:03:01','2014-10-27 01:07:57',NULL),(6421,'Brisbane hit by golf ball-sized hail storms','brisbane-hit-by-golf-ball-sized-hail-storms','Brisbane hit by golf ball-sized hail storms','<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/storm.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6422\" title=\"storm\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/storm.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"352\" /></a>\r\n\r\nGOLF ball-sized hailstones, destructive winds and torrential rain are battering parts of Brisbane. The weather bureau has issued a severe warning for Brisbane city, Ipswich, Logan, Redland and Moreton Bay. An Energex spokesman confirmed at least 82,000 homes were without power, most of which were in Brisbane and its surrounds. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/environment/brisbane-hit-by-golf-ball-sized-hail-storms/story-e6frflp0-1227137381983\">news.com.au</a>\r\n\r\n</div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6421','2014-10-12 01:20:13','2014-11-27 14:17:49',NULL),(6425,'Planned System Maintance And Upgrade - 28/11/2014','planned-system-maintance-and-upgrade-28112014','Planned System Maintance And Upgrade - 28/11/2014','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/AMG-Mercedes.jpg\"><img title=\"AMG Mercedes\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/AMG-Mercedes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"302\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Important notice:\r\n28/11/2014 7:00 pm Sydney time\r\nCrashzone server upgrade</strong>\r\n\r\nTonight and over the weekend we will be making significant improvements to the Crashzone system including upgrading the server that run Crashzone. The changes will increase the speed and reliability of the system and accommodate customer demand for the future. If you experience any issues with the Crashzone system please help by reporting the problem to support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6425','2014-10-12 01:30:43','2014-11-28 11:07:13',NULL),(6428,'Barn Find in France Turns up 60 Classic Cars','barn-find-in-france-turns-up-60-classic-cars','Barn Find in France Turns up 60 Classic Cars','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/barn-find.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6429\" title=\"barn find\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/barn-find.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"340\" /></a>\r\n\r\nYou’d be lucky to stumble onto a single classic car out in an old barn. But in the case of Artcurial Motorcars in France, they’ve hit the motherload, stumbling onto a property that was home to 60 rare and collectible cars. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://95octane.com/2014/12/08/france-classic-car-barn-find/\">www.95octane.com</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6428','2014-10-12 01:35:47','2014-12-12 01:22:21',NULL),(6434,'Kiwi couple ‘trapped’ in keyless entry car','kiwi-couple-%e2%80%98trapped%e2%80%99-in-keyless-entry-car','Kiwi couple ‘trapped’ in keyless entry car','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mazda3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6435\" title=\"mazda3\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/mazda3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /></a>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">After getting back in the car about 7pm to go watch some local fireworks, they realised they had not brought the electronic transponder (which replaced traditional key systems) with them.The doors automatically locked.They’d left the new user’s manual in the house.They couldn’t find a manual override.Both became convinced they were trapped. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/real-life/kiwi-couple-trapped-in-keyless-entry-car/story-fnq2o7dd-1227159245130\">www.news.com.au</a></span></div>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6434','2014-10-12 01:38:06','2014-12-19 01:13:25',NULL),(6438,'MERRY CHRISTMAS 2014','merry-christmas-2014','MERRY CHRISTMAS 2014','<img src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2007/12/crashzone-christmas.JPG\" alt=\"Merry Christmas\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><em>MERRY CHRISTMAS</em></strong>\r\n\r\nA big thank you to everyone that has supported Crashzone for 2014. We hope that you have a good rest and get ready for a productive 2015. From all the staff at Crashzone, Merry Christmas and best wishes for the holiday season.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6438','2014-12-25 01:49:04','2014-12-25 01:49:04',NULL),(6441,'Crashzone system update ','crashzone-system-update-4','Crashzone system update ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/cz-xmas.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6442\" title=\"cz-xmas\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/cz-xmas.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"350\" height=\"130\" /></a>\r\n\r\nCrashzone customers,\r\n\r\nwww.crashzone.com.au has had an update over the Christmas period with a few bug fixes and a few new functions as listed below.\r\n\r\n1. Fix Bug:Copy Photos doesn’t copy to blank Quotes\r\n2. Fix Bug: Pnet send Status function in detail page now working.\r\n3. Fix Bug: Arnie RACT Branch now will working\r\n4. Details page, Date in/out now will popup calendar to choose from.\r\n5. Emailing notes from detail pages.Email will have Job Number in Subject <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Line\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">6. New Feature: Emailing “select images” for parts order now will working\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">7.Pnet Get Authorised message now will import customer Mobile into in Detail Page.\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">8. New Timer Reporting Page with Edit Function for Time App</span>\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or issues with the update please contact us at support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6441','2014-12-29 02:03:48','2014-12-29 02:03:48',NULL),(6453,'BMW Uses Frickin’ Lasers for High Beams ','bmw-uses-frickin%e2%80%99-lasers-for-high-beams','BMW Uses Frickin’ Lasers for High Beams ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/BMW-Laser.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6455\" title=\"BMW Laser\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/BMW-Laser.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"537\" height=\"334\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe whole process creates light that’s ten times more intense than today’s xenon, halogen, or LED headlights—all while consuming 30 percent less energy. And BMW has some nifty tricks to keep that laser-derived light from blinding oncoming drivers.\r\nFor the full story please visit <a href=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/bmw-uses-frickin-lasers-for-high-beams-that-dont-blind/\">http://blog.caranddriver.com/</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6453','2015-01-04 03:23:55','2015-01-15 03:27:41',NULL),(6459,'Lamborghini Huracan crashes at 320km/h ','lamborghini-huracan-crashes-at-320kmh','Lamborghini Huracan crashes at 320km/h ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Lambocrash.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6460\" title=\"Lambocrash\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Lambocrash.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"338\" /></a>\r\n\r\nA Lamborghini owner decided to test the limits of his car by driving it at 340km/h, until he hit a bump in the road and got airborne. For the full story and video please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/innovation/lamborghini-huracan-crashes-at-320kmh-on-hungary-highway/story-fnjwucvh-1227191842395\">news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6459','2015-01-04 04:00:50','2015-01-21 04:07:49',NULL),(6464,'Spam email issues with Trend micro','spam-email-issues-with-trend-micro','Spam email issues with Trend micro','<strong>Important Notice:\r\n22/01/2015  11:00am\r\n</strong><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Spam emails:</strong>\r\n\r\nCrashzone is having issues with some companies that are using trend micro for their spam email filter. This is causing your outgoing email to be blocked which means it will not be received. The two main companies that we have reports of issues with are Zurich Insurance and Trivett Australia.\r\n\r\nCrashzone is working to rectify the issue but in the interim if you have an email that is getting blocked we suggest that your forward the email to yourself and then re forward it from your own mail client.\r\n\r\nAny questions or further help please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6464','2015-01-04 04:05:59','2015-01-22 03:13:58',NULL),(6467,'CCRN first annual conference breakfast - 18/4/15 Bookings essential ','ccrn-first-annual-conference-breakfast-17415-bookings-essential','CCRN first annual conference breakfast - 18/4/15 Bookings essential ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/CCRNO-logo.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6471\" title=\"CCRNO logo\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/CCRNO-logo.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"180\" height=\"183\" /></a>\r\n<strong>Crashzone Community Repairer Network (CCRN) first annual conference breakfast</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>When</strong>: Saturday the 18th of April 2015 7:00am to 10:00am\r\n<strong>Where:</strong> The Deck, crn of Flinders and King St  ( short walk to the Collision repair Expo afterwards )\r\n<strong>Cost:</strong> $30.00 per head ( to cover food &amp; venue )\r\n\r\nTo coincide with the Collision Repair Expo the CCRN will host it’s first community repairer conference in Melbourne, we will have a number of guest speakers including\r\n\r\n* Gary Steele- EZI- Methods\r\n* Dave Taylor-PartsCheck\r\n* A 3rd party specialist - recovery work\r\n* Sam Burt- Quoting for fun or for profit\r\n* Gavin McGahey - Planning plus\r\n* I-Car Matt Perkins\r\n\r\nBuffet breakfast from 645am, speakers 7.30am sharp\r\n\r\nlimited to repairers that book and pay.\r\n\r\nCCRN\r\nBendigo Bank\r\nBSB: 633 000\r\nAccount: 153934708\r\n\r\nplease use your shop name as the reference number, and email your receipt/confirmation to ccrn@crashzone.com.au\r\n\r\nOn conclusion of the conference we will walk down to the Collision Repair Expo as a group ( optional )\r\n\r\nHope to see you there.\r\n\r\nCrashzone Community Repairer Network',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6467','2015-04-16 01:00:09','2015-04-16 01:43:51',NULL),(6483,'Holden maintains title as Victoria’s most commonly stolen vehicle','holden-maintains-title-as-victoria%e2%80%99s-most-commonly-stolen-vehicle','Holden maintains title as Victoria’s most commonly stolen vehicle','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/xHolden-SS-V.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6484\" title=\"xHolden-SS-V\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/xHolden-SS-V.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"293\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHolden was Victoria’s most commonly stolen vehicle make in 2014, according to the latest data released today from Victoria Police. For the full story please visit www.caradvice.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6483','2015-03-20 09:56:55','2015-03-20 09:56:55',NULL),(6489,' Cactus good for shopping centers ','cactus-good-for-shopping-centers',' Cactus good for shopping centers ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/xCitroen-C4-Cactus.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6490\" title=\"xCitroen-C4-Cactus\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/xCitroen-C4-Cactus.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"293\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe C4 Cactus features unique thermo plastic urethane ‘Airbumps’ that form a flexible skin to guard from minor impacts and scratches. These can be had in a selection of contrasting colours that are yet to be finalized for Australia. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/343967/2016-citroen-c4-cactus-here-early-next-year/\">www.caradvice.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6489','2015-03-24 07:57:20','2015-03-24 07:57:20',NULL),(6494,'Ford automatic speed limiting ','ford-automatic-speed-limiting','Ford automatic speed limiting ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Speed-limiter.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6495\" title=\"Speed limiter\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Speed-limiter.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"370\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe system uses a forward-facing camera mounted high on the windscreen, which is capable of interpreting speed limit signs, and sets the car’s speed limiter accordingly. On country roads where speed limit signs are sparsely located or non-existent, the system will use speed limit data stored in the car’s satellite navigation unit. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.caradvice.com.au/344509/ford-s-max-debuts-automatic-speed-limiting-technology-that-reads-road-signs/\">www.caradvice.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6494','2015-03-26 02:28:33','2015-03-26 02:28:33',NULL),(6498,'Holden brings back the Sandman','holden-brings-back-the-sandman','Holden brings back the Sandman','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Sandman.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6499\" title=\"Sandman\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Sandman.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /></a>\r\n\r\nTHE Holden Sandman is back 40 years after it was introduced, minus the fluffy dice and heart-shaped windows — but with the shagpile carpet and brightly coloured stickers that made the original famous. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/innovation/holden-brings-back-the-sandman-complete-with-orange-shagpile-carpet