rouble keeping pace. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/innovation/porsche-kia-top-list-as-car-quality-rankings-throw-up-some-surprises/story-fnjwucvh-1227403288367\">www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6723','2015-06-18 01:33:49','2015-06-18 01:33:49',NULL),(6727,'Bitter ex cuts possessions in half, posts them on eBay','bitter-ex-cuts-possessions-in-half-posts-them-on-ebay','Bitter ex cuts possessions in half, posts them on eBay','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/half-car.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6728\" title=\"half car\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/half-car.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /></a>\r\n\r\nliterally cut his possessions in half, in a bid to spite his former partner. She reportedly received her share in the post, while he’s listed his halves on eBay. For the full story visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/online/bitter-ex-cuts-possessions-in-half-posts-them-on-ebay/story-fnjwmwrh-1227404203751\">www.news.com.au </a>\r\nCut and shut anybody ?',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6727','2015-06-19 01:49:42','2015-06-19 01:49:42',NULL),(6732,'‘Safety Truck’ Features a Camera and Live View Display','%e2%80%98safety-truck%e2%80%99-features-a-camera-and-live-view-display','‘Safety Truck’ Features a Camera and Live View Display','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/samsungsafetytruck.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6733\" title=\"samsungsafetytruck\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/samsungsafetytruck.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"359\" /></a>\r\n\r\nSamsung wants to help make roads safer by incorporating some camera technology into semi-trailer trucks. By adding a front camera and a giant rear “live view” display to the trucks, Samsung’s ‘Safety Truck’ project makes it easier for drivers to see “through” the trucks and know when it’s safe to pass. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://petapixel.com/2015/06/20/samsungs-safety-truck-features-a-camera-and-live-view-display/\">www.petapixel.com</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6732','2015-06-22 01:54:10','2015-06-22 01:54:10',NULL),(6738,'VicRoads recommends cyclists be blameless in any crash with a driver','vicroads-recommends-cyclists-be-blameless-in-any-crash-with-a-driver','VicRoads recommends cyclists be blameless in any crash with a driver','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/2bikes.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6739\" title=\"2bikes\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/2bikes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /></a>\r\n\r\nCYCLISTS should be blameless in any crash involving drivers, an independent report into overhauling Victoria’s road rules recommends.It was also suggested police be given powers to issue on-the-spot fines to cyclists who ride while talking on their mobile phone and riders not in single file on windy and narrow roads.A host of changes to road rules has been recommended to VicRoads as part of the wide ranging cycling road rules review it commissioned. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/national/victoria/report-to-vicroads-recommends-cyclists-be-blameless-in-any-crash-with-a-driver/story-fnii5sms-1227413057481\">www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6738','2015-06-25 01:02:33','2015-06-25 01:02:33',NULL),(6742,'Mass breakdown in Sydney due to dodgy petrol','mass-breakdown-in-sydney-due-to-dodgy-petrol','Mass breakdown in Sydney due to dodgy petrol','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/petrol.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6744\" title=\"petrol\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/petrol.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /></a>\r\n\r\nMore than 20 cars broke down on the M4 this morning after filling up with E10 petrol at a Sydney service station.The cars filled up at the Caltex service station on the city-bound side near Prospect before being forced to pull into the breakdown lane between Eastern Creek and the Prospect Highway. For the full story please visit<a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/national/mass-breakdown-in-sydney-due-to-dodgy-petrol/story-fncynjr2-1227413865907\"> www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6742','2015-06-26 03:05:44','2015-06-26 03:05:44',NULL),(6746,'Partscheck','partscheck','Partscheck','Crashzone works with Parts Check for parts prices and ordering. Send a parts list to PartsCheck and receive the part numbers and prices directly back into Crashzone. No more typing part numbers. Get accurate list and trade prices for you quote. Visit <a href=\"http://www.partscheck.com.au/global/index.php\">www.partscheck.com.au</a> and setup a free account.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"../wp-content/uploads/2012/01/CZ-Partscheck.jpg\"><img title=\"CZ Partscheck\" src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2012/01/CZ-Partscheck.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"184\" /></a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6746','2015-06-30 06:32:10','2015-06-30 06:33:09',NULL),(6752,'How to add images by email ','how-to-add-images-by-email','How to add images by email ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ21.jpg\"><img title=\"CZ2\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ21.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"158\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>You can add images to the quote using your email:</strong>\r\n\r\n* Open a new email\r\n* Type in you Crashzone email address ( find your CZ address in the settings )\r\n* Type the Crashzone quote number into the subject i.e ( 5013 ) <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">only the number </span>\r\n* Attach images to the email\r\n* Send email\r\n* Images will now attach to the quote  ( the process takes approx 1 minute )\r\n* Click on the details tab to refresh the system and load the new images\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ11.jpg\"><img title=\"CZ1\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ11.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"275\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor help with images please contact <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/contact-us\">support@crashzone.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6752','2015-07-01 04:27:36','2015-07-01 04:27:36',NULL),(6756,'Dubai is a dumping ground for expensive cars','dubai-is-a-dumping-ground-for-expensive-cars','Dubai is a dumping ground for expensive cars','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/dumped-car-e1435885291270.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6757\" title=\"dumped car\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/dumped-car-e1435885291270.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn the last five years, luxury cars including Porsches, Ferraris and Mercedes Benz have been abandoned on the streets of Dubai and left at airport parking lots as their owners flee bankruptcy, hit by the financial crisis. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/travel/travel-ideas/dubai-is-a-dumping-ground-for-expensive-cars/story-fnjpja3r-1227425315006\">www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6756','2015-07-03 04:04:53','2015-07-03 04:04:53',NULL),(6760,'Crashzone – It’s Free','crashzone-its-free','Crashzone – It’s Free','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/smash-monaro-quoted-on-crashzone.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6761\" title=\"smash-monaro-quoted-on-crashzone\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/smash-monaro-quoted-on-crashzone.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"278\" /></a>\r\n\r\nCrashzone is a web based quoting system for Smash Repairers accessed by secure login using a user name and password ( the same as internet banking )\r\nBeing web based allows you to access Crashzone from any computer, laptop, note book or mobile device that has internet access. This allows you to use the latest technology such as the Apple iPad and iPhone.\r\n\r\nFast and simple to use, writes quotes, add images, create tax and excess invoices, email and print your quote. Crashzone is accepted by all insurance companies.\r\n\r\nCrashzone is 100% FREE we don’t charge you anything and there are no catches. There are no support fees or extra modules to buy, everything is included such as integration with ORM, PNET, ARNIE &amp; Estimage.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6760','2016-05-19 00:00:28','2016-05-19 08:25:25',NULL),(6764,'How to -  delete a supplementary quote','how-to-delete-a-supplementary-quote','How to -  delete a supplementary quote','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Crashzone-delete-supp-quotes.jpg\"><img title=\"Crashzone delete supp quotes\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Crashzone-delete-supp-quotes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n\r\nTo delete a supplementary quote click on the “Delete Supp button”\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>From the quote page go into the supplementary quote you want to delete</li>\r\n	<li>click on the “Delete Supp button”</li>\r\n	<li>This will delete the supplementary quote from the systemPlease note that the delete sup button only appears when you are in a supplementary quote.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor help or questions please contact support@crashzone.com.au',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6764','2015-07-13 05:32:07','2015-07-13 05:32:07',NULL),(6770,'Crashzone iPhone App ','crashzone-iphone-app-5','Crashzone iPhone App ','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/iPhoneCZ1.jpg\"><img title=\"Crashzone iPhone App\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/iPhoneCZ1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"380\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe application allow you to take photos with you iPhone and instantly upload them to your Crashzone quote.\r\n\r\n* Download the application from the App store\r\n* Compatible with iPhone 4 and above\r\n* To setup enter you company ID number in the setting\r\n* Take photos with the App\r\n\r\nYour ID can be found in the Crashzone Settings page.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6770','2015-07-16 01:24:10','2015-07-16 01:24:10',NULL),(6773,'Ford developing new advanced headlights','ford-developing-new-advanced-headlights','Ford developing new advanced headlights','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1437434779607.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6774\" title=\"Ford advanced headlights \" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1437434779607.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"238\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFord is developing new safety headlights that utilise on board cameras, GPS and infrared cameras to increase driver awareness while driving at night.\r\nThe American brand\'s Advanced Front Lighting System uses on board cameras to widen headlight beams when approaching a junction or roundabout so as to illuminate any hazards approaching.\r\nCoupled with this Ford is developing infrared camera based spot lighting to highlight pedestrians, cyclists and large animals on the road up to 120 metres. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.drive.com.au/motor-news/ford-developing-new-advanced-headlights-20150720-gigcf2.html\">www.drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6773','2015-07-21 02:59:28','2015-07-21 02:59:28',NULL),(6777,'Jeep hacking provokes recall of 1.4 million cars','jeep-hacking-provokes-recall-of-1-4-million-cars','Jeep hacking provokes recall of 1.4 million cars','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/jeep.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6779\" title=\"jeep\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/jeep.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"255\" /></a>\r\n\r\nA test arranged by US tech outlet Wired saw two \"white hat\" hackers disable a moving Jeep to prove security in its internet-cable UConnect stereo system was not sufficient.\r\nExperts were able to break into the car\'s systems and take control of the engine, brakes and steering. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.drive.com.au/motor-news/jeep-hacking-provokes-recall-of-14-million-cars-20150726-gil089.html\">www.drive.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6777','2015-07-27 03:07:41','2015-07-27 03:07:41',NULL),(6782,'How to add images by email','how-to-add-images-by-email-2','How to add images by email','<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ21.jpg\"><img title=\"CZ2\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ21.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"158\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>You can add images to the quote using your email:</strong>\r\n\r\n* Open a new email\r\n* Type in you Crashzone email address ( find your CZ address in the settings )\r\n* Type the Crashzone quote number into the subject i.e ( 5013 ) only the number\r\n* Attach images to the email\r\n* Send email\r\n* Images will now attach to the quote  ( the process takes approx 1 minute )\r\n* Click on the details tab to refresh the system and load the new images\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ11.jpg\"><img title=\"CZ1\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CZ11.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"275\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor help with images please contact <a href=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/contact-us\">support@crashzone.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=6782','2015-