uploads/2017/05/8-26-2016-11-42-57-AM.jpg\" alt=\"8-26-2016 11-42-57 AM\" width=\"529\" height=\"379\" />\r\n\r\nHi Everyone,\r\n\r\nWe made some updates to the Crashzone home page last night. If possible on your browsers clear the cookies and cache to make sure you are getting all the latest changes. If you are experiencing any issues with the website or login please contact support@crashzone.com.au or phone 02 9011 6647.',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=7220','2017-05-11 18:10:06','2017-05-11 18:11:32',NULL),(7225,'Ransomware cyberattack hits Australia','ransomware-cyberattack-hits-australia','Ransomware cyberattack hits Australia','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7226\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/ransom.jpg\" alt=\"ransom\" width=\"600\" height=\"353\" />\r\n\r\nA MASSIVE cyber attack which has hit 200,000 people in at least 150 countries has claimed its first Australian victims and authorities warn more is yet to come.The Federal Government has confirmed three private businesses have been hit by the unprecedented ransomware attack, which wormed its way into thousands of computer systems around the world in an apparent extortion plot, shutting users out unless they coughed up payment.\r\n\r\nFor the full story please visit<a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/online/hacking/cyber-attack-in-australia-2017-business-hit-by-ransomware/news-story/598e9382bcff0c12ca3e84f960ed8dc1\"> news.com.au</a>\r\n\r\nMake sure you computer operating systems are fully updated and be careful opening any unknown attachments on your computer.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/portal/Threat/Encyclopedia/Entry.aspx?Name=Ransom:Win32/WannaCrypt\">https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/portal/Threat/Encyclopedia/Entry.aspx?Name=Ransom:Win32/WannaCrypt</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=7225','2017-05-14 16:34:30','2017-05-14 16:34:30',NULL),(7230,'New Code of Conduct effective 1st of May 2017','new-code-conduct-effective-1st-may-2017','New Code of Conduct effective 1st of May 2017','<a href=\"http://autointegrity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Motor-vehicle-insurance-and-repair-industry-Code-of-Conduct.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1905\" src=\"http://autointegrity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Motor-vehicle-insurance-and-repair-industry-Code-of-Conduct.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 364px) 100vw, 364px\" srcset=\"http://autointegrity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Motor-vehicle-insurance-and-repair-industry-Code-of-Conduct.jpg 364w, http://autointegrity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Motor-vehicle-insurance-and-repair-industry-Code-of-Conduct-300x190.jpg 300w\" alt=\"\" width=\"364\" height=\"230\" /></a>\r\n\r\nNSW GOVERNMENT DRIVES NEW SMASH REPAIR CODE\r\nThe new code came into effect as of the 1st May 2017\r\n\r\nThe NSW Government has championed the cause of up to 5 million licensed drivers across the State by overseeing the implementation of a new mandatory Code of Conduct, signed off by the motor vehicle insurance and repair industry.\r\n\r\nFor more information click on the link below.\r\n<a href=\"http://autointegrity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Code-Media-release.pdf\">Code Media release</a>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to view the latest code click the link below:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.abrcode.com.au/\">http://www.abrcode.com.au/</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=7230','2017-05-18 22:01:50','2017-05-18 22:01:50',NULL),(7232,'The Perfect Storm Hits Used-Car Values','perfect-storm-hits-used-car-values','The Perfect Storm Hits Used-Car Values','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7234\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/20170521_cars13-e1495428257855.jpg\" alt=\"20170521_cars13\" width=\"600\" height=\"457\" />\r\n\r\nI stand here today as witness to a perfect storm that could make a 50% reduction in used car values a very real possibility. I have already witnessed signs that the truck and SUV market have corrected. The manufacturer\'s’ incentive response to a growing day-supply problem along with the supercharged discounting effect of more dealers fighting over fewer sales is the equivalent of dropping the MOAB on used car value.\r\n\r\nFor the full story visit <a href=\"http://www.zerohedge.com/news/2017-05-21/perfect-storm-hits-used-car-values-foundation-auto-industry-faltering\">zerohedge.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=7232','2017-05-21 21:44:51','2017-05-21 21:44:51',NULL),(7237,'Motorists “not necessarily ready” to embrace driverless cars','motorists-not-necessarily-ready-embrace-driverless-cars','Motorists “not necessarily ready” to embrace driverless cars','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7238\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/FordDriverless-e1496187177283.jpg\" alt=\"FordDriverless\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n\r\nDespite ploughing billions globally into the new technology, the boss of Ford’s local operation has admitted that Australians are “not ready” for driverless cars and it will be a struggle to persuade them to buy new vehicles. For the full story please visit <a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/technology/innovation/motoring/ford-australia-chief-says-motorists-not-necessarily-ready-to-embrace-driverless-cars/news-story/2ab7dccf79c434e004c629a6baf26097\">www.news.com.au</a>',0,0,2,'publish','open','http://www.crashzone.com.au/?p=7237','2017-05-30 16:34:12','2017-05-30 16:34:12',NULL),(7247,'Crashzone photo app for Apple','crashzone-photo-app-apple','Crashzone photo app for Apple','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7248\" src=\"http://www.crashzone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/iPhoneCZ1.jpg\" alt=\"iPhoneCZ1\" width=\"590\" height=\"380\" />\r\n\r\nThe application allows  you to take photos with you iPhone and instantly upload them to your Crashzone quote.\r\n\r\n* Download t